title: cheese ball
directions: Cut 2 packs dried beef into small pieces and add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into two balls.
Cut up the rest of the dried beef and roll ball into it.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a square pan.

title: very special brisket
directions: Rub meat with salt and garlic salt. Mix everything together and pour on meat.
Line pan or dish with aluminum foil and cover with aluminum foil.
Marinate 24 hours in refrigerator.
Cook in foil 10 hours at 250°.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Grease an oblong pan.
Mix yellow cake mix, a stick of butter and 1 egg.
Press in pan.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, 2 eggs and vanilla.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Beat eggs; stir in whipping cream and butter. Gradually add sugar mixture, stirring in corn. Pour into greased 13 x 9 dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Heat oven to 350°. Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift together dry ingredients into mixing bowl. Add remaining ingredients and blend well. Drop by teaspoon onto a slightly greased baking sheet. Bake 15 to 18 minutes. Cool before removing from sheet. Makes 48 to 50 cookies.

title: shrimp and crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together with the softened cream cheese. Serve with chips, etc.

title: danish prune bar cookies
directions: Mix well the prunes, nuts, brown sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold into eggs.
Spread into greased 7 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Cut into small bars and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 24 bars.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger with onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix ingredients together and form into balls.
Put into greased casserole.
Cover with Saran Wrap and put into microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain off grease.
Add cream of celery and French onion soup.
Pour over meatballs and mix lightly.
Heat about another 3 to 4 minutes covered with Saran Wrap.
Serve over rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Slightly cook and drain spinach.
Mix cream cheese into spinach, along with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Put in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Cover top completely with sour cream and paprika.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add butter or margarine cut into small pieces and milk.
Stir and microwave 3 minutes.
Stir and cook 2 minutes more.
Add vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch dish.

title: ham spread
directions: Mix together and spread on crackers.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in clear serving dish with cover. Keep in refrigerator until served.

title: orange slice brownies
directions: Cream eggs and sugar until light. Add vanilla. Add chopped candy and nuts to flour.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: banana coffee bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in banana.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: In large, heavy pan brown meat and onion.
Quarter, core and cut cabbage into 1-inch strips (about 8 cups).
Add to meat, cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally until cabbage wilts. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cupcakes
directions: Mix thoroughly cream cheese, egg, sugar, salt and chocolate chips; set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, salt, baking soda, water, oil and vinegar together; put in cupcake papers.
Top with cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle on top 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini pineapple nut bread
directions: Beat together eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Then stir in zucchini, flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking powder, raisins, nuts and crushed pineapple.

title: winter salad
directions: Combine corn syrup, peanut oil, vinegar, dry mustard, garlic salt and pepper in a large jar.
Cover tightly and shake until thoroughly blended.
In a large bowl, combine cabbage, carrots, beets and onions. Pour dressing over vegetables and toss well. Chill before serving.

title: school days peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together the shortening, sugar and peanut butter.
Add flour and vanilla extract.
Knead until dough will no longer adhere.
Add boiling water; knead until dough is completely adhered, smooth and shiny.
Make into balls; place 12 balls of dough onto cookie sheet.
Press each cookie with a fork.
Do not grease cookie sheet.
Place into preheated oven and bake at 300° for approximately 20 minutes, or until light golden brown.
Yields approximately 8 dozen cookies.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: cloverleaf rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in water; add to first mixture.
Add egg and enough flour so dough can be kneaded on board.
Roll in small balls.
Put 3 in each muffin pan that has been greased.
Cover and let rise to double in size.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: orange apricot salad
directions: Heat apricot juice to boiling. Mix with Jell-O. Beat cream cheese and Cool Whip and fold into the Jell-O mixture. Pour over arranged oranges in gelatin mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, combine brown sugar, eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir into batter. Stir in oats, chocolate chips and raisins.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Put layer of chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan or long casserole dish; top with layer of chips.
(You can use one layer or two.) Melt cheese; add soups and Ro-Tel.
Stir to mix well.
Pour over chicken and chips.
Bake at 300° or 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: brassadella
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Make a well in the center.
Pour in butter, eggs and lemon.
Mix thoroughly, kneading well so it is smooth.
If dough won't hold together, add some milk.
Should be the consistency of pie dough or a cookie dough that could be rolled out.
Should be stiff enough to hold its shape.
Shape the dough in a circle, like a wreath.
Place in a buttered 9-inch round cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Slice for serving.
Serve as a cookie or biscuit with wine.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to	package directions.
In a punch bowl or other large bowl, crumble
1/3 of the cake.
Layer 1/3 of the remaining ingredients in the following order:
pudding, pineapple with juice, coconut,
cherry
pie filling, Cool Whip and pecans. Repeat the	layers	two
more
times, ending with Cool Whip sprinkled with pecans.
Chill.
Yields 30 servings.

title: hot cider
directions: Simmer 1/2 hour. Don't boil.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together cocoa, flour and sugar.
Add egg yolks and milk. Cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites for meringue.

title: pea salad
directions: Cook peas as directed.
Drain.
Cool.
In large bowl, combine peas, cheese, eggs, onion and pimento.
In small bowl, combine salad dressing, salt, sauce and pepper.
Add to pea mixture.
Toss to combine.
Cover.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Stir mixture well before serving.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Put cheese on last of baking time.

title: chocolate cream cheese frosting
directions: Work cream cheese with a spoon until very soft.
Blend in the cooled melted chocolate and gradually add the sugar, beating until smooth after each addition.
Add salt and vanilla and stir in enough cream to give a smooth spreading consistency.
Spread on cooled cake.
Makes enough for two 8-inch cake layers.

title: fermented fruit starter
directions: Mix the pineapple, 1 cup sugar and alcohol in a one gallon crock, apothecary jar or other wide mouth contianer, cover loosely and place in a cool spot.
Do not refrigerate and do not cover tightly.
Gases from the fermentation could cause an accident. Stir lightly once or twice a week.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt; gradually add milk. Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils. Cook 2 minutes and remove from heat. Add small amount of egg yolks; stir into remaining hot mixture. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add butter and vanilla; cool slightly. Line Pyrex baking dish with vanilla wafers, layer of bananas, mixture, then layer of bananas, ending with vanilla wafers.

title: tina's cornbread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir in remaining ingredients just until smooth.
Bake at 450° in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Toothpick test about 20 to 25 minutes to see if toothpick comes out clean.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Microwave the first 3 ingredients for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds or until chocolate is completely melted, then spread it over the crust.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes or until chocolate is firm, then arrange bananas over the chocolate. Then mix the pudding mix with the milk in a large bowl, using a whisk (about 1 minute).
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon over bananas in crust.
Spread with whipped topping.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or until ready to serve.
Enjoy.

title: oven pancakes
directions: Combine flour, eggs and dash of salt.
Pour in skillet.
Bake at 425° in oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with powdered sugar, syrup or lemon juice.
Makes 2 servings.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute vegetables in oil until tender; add tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer for 15 minutes; add shrimp.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Put on top of warm cake.
Place under broiler and brown top.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into a tube pan.
Bake at 325° until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Cool.
Boil sugar and evaporated milk for 5 minutes.
Cool and add Angel Flake coconut.
Spread between layers.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Mix the first five ingredients together in a pan.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the marshmallows and peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and let cool.

title: amaretto
directions: Boil sugar and water for 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.

title: baked crab meat and shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumbs; place in individual seashells or in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, milk and cocoa in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Add oats and peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cool and eat!

title: fillet elegante
directions: Thaw fillets (sole, orange roughy, haddock or halibut), enough to separate.
Arrange in buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Dash with pepper.
Dot with butter.
Spread soup over fillets; sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 25 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix lemon juice, egg yolks and milk.
Pour in graham cracker crumb crust.
Beat egg whites until frothy, then add sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Pour over lemon mixture.
Bake at 350° until meringue is brown.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: baked corn dish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in covered dish until center sets.

title: rice krispies chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted margarine.
Roll in crushed Rice Krispies.
Place in pan and pour 1 glass of water over chicken. Bake for 45 minutes.
Cover with foil.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.
Do not turn chicken.

title: spring casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until crispy tender.
Drain and place in 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Top with turkey slices.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over turkey.
Top with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with onion rings.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked ham slice
directions: Place ham in shallow glass dish.
Spread mustard on top and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Cover.

title: apple cake
directions: Put oil and sugar in bowl; mix together.
Add one egg at a time.
In another bowl, mix flour, salt and soda and add to oil mixture.
Add pecans, apples and coconut.
Add vanilla last.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: banana cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla (mix well).
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together. Add to shortening mixture.
Add bananas and nuts.
Drop cookies by teaspoonfuls onto a greased pan.
Sprinkle with sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: my hero sandwich
directions: Cut French bread into 12 slices.
Combine cheese, olives, onion, mushrooms, oil, tomato sauce and oregano in bowl.
Mix well.
Spread on French bread; place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° to 400° just until bubbly.

title: pizza dough
directions: Add yeast to warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt and oil.
Add flour.
Mix by hand or in food processor.
Spray bowl with a little oil.
Let rise for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Bake at 400°.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Combine eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Add bread; stir. Add cheese and sausage.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut and serve.
Serves 6.

title: caramel-filled chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, cocoa powder and baking soda.

title: celery soup
directions: Remove leaves from celery stalks; reserve leaves for garnish. Place half of celery and 1 cup buttermilk in blender.
Add half of the green onions, salt and pepper to blender.
Scrape celery mixture into a large metal bowl.
Repeat with remaining celery, buttermilk and green onions.
Stir in ice water.
Refrigerate. Garnish.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter a baking dish.
Add the 6 to 8 sliced apples.
Pour 1/3 cup melted butter and 1/2 cup sugar over apple slices.
Then mix the flour, remaining sugar, baking powder and egg.
Mix until crumbs form, then put mixture over apples. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 2 tablespoons syrup to make custard. Combine reserved syrup, egg yolks, sugar, vinegar, butter or margarine and salt in small honkey saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat about 6 minutes or until mixture thickens slightly and coats spoon.
Cool to room temperature in a large bowl.
Combine pineapple, cherries, oranges and marshmallows.
Pour custard over. Mix fruit mixture gently.
Whip the whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Fold whipping cream into fruit mixture, turn serving bowl. Cover and refrigerate 24 hours or overnight.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: prohibition steaks
directions: Season steaks with salt, pepper and garlic.
Heat butter in large skillet.
Add steaks, saute 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until desired doneness.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.

title: tamale casserole
directions: In a casserole dish layer bottom with crushed chips.
Unwrap tamales and slice on top of chips.
Layer remaining ingredients and top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Split and arrange muffins on a baking sheet.
Combine tomato sauce, salt, pepper, oregano, Italian seasoning and garlic salt in a bowl.
Coat muffins with tomato mixture.
Sprinkle on cheese. Broil until cheese is bubbly.
Remove and serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple.
Add the milk.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: lima bean soup
directions: Soak the lima beans in water overnight to soften or boil on stove top until soft.
In a large saucepan, brown the bacon together with the onion.
Drain excess grease.
Add lima beans, tomatoes, bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Simmer until beans are tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Top each bowl with Parmesan cheese to serve.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Mix eggs, melted butter and vanilla. Add dry ingredients. Pour into 8-inch square, microwave-proof dish. Bake on High for 5 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Make a pocket in each pork chop. Cook bacon pieces in skillet over medium heat until crisp. Remove from heat and drain. Stir in stuffing crumbs and water until mixed well. Stir in cheese. Sprinkle both sides of pork chops with seasoned salt, marjoram and pepper. Fill pockets with corn bread mixture. Cook in same skillet over medium, turning once until brown. Place pork chops in ungreased pan, cover tightly with foil. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake about 15 minutes longer or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake until brown at 325°.

title: pure fruit punch
directions: Mix together hot water, sugar and frozen lemonade.
Then add pineapple juice, orange juice and ginger ale.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine
ingredients
(do
not	drain
salmon),
except additional crumbs and margarine.
Mix with fork until blended. Shape into 9
patties,
using 1/4 cup each.
Flatten slightly. Dip into
additional
fine
crumbs.
Preheat
frypan
to 320°. Melt butter.
Add patties; brown, turn and brown on other side (about 10 minutes total).	Serve with chili sauce or catsup or tartar sauce.
Garnish with parsley.

title: cherry frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in a 9 x 13 casserole dish.

title: shipwreck picnic casserole
directions: Butter a very large casserole dish (3 to 4-quart).
Layer ingredients as listed.
Meat will be in center.
Season each layer to taste with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours (longer if cold).

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar. In separate bowl, mix pudding and milk slowly.
Add pudding to cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Make macaroni and cheese according to directions.
Add ground beef, soup and milk.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes.

title: baked stuffed scallops
directions: Place scallops (any other good fish may be used) in greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Melt margarine, then add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Press dressing over fish, covering well.
Before baking, cover baking dish with foil and remove for last 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cherry dessert
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine wafer crumbs with melted margarine. Press into the bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Place in freezer for 10 minutes.
In another bowl, combine sour cream, pudding and milk.
Beat on low for 1 1/2 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Spoon pie filling on top.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: spinach casserole
directions: A healthy dish that kids really like!

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Dice chicken and roll in flour and spices and brown in oil. Add onion and bell pepper and continue to cook 5 minutes. Simmer 20 minutes until rice is tender. Add okra and cook until okra is done, approximately 10 minutes.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Combine chicken, eggs, mayo, onion, mushrooms and celery.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, place bread, butter side down.
Spread chicken mixture evenly.
Combine soup, sour cream and pimiento; mix well.
Place another row of bread and pour soup and sour cream mix over top.
Top with almonds.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel apples and slice them thin.
Put them in a rather shallow 1-quart casserole dish and sprinkle them with water.
Put aside while you prepare the crust.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw peaches beforehand.
Melt 1 stick of oleo in oven in Pyrex dish.
Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and milk.
Pour over melted margarine in baking dish.
Put thawed peaches on top of the batter.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and pour 3/4 cup water over all.
Cook 40 to 50 minutes or until crust is browned.

title: dirt cake
directions: First mixture: Combine melted margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.

title: roka cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients, except walnuts.
Form into balls.
Roll balls in walnuts and cover.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: apple or peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 8 by 11 inch square baking dish at 350°. Combine all ingredients in the dish; bake for 30 to 45 minutes. Let cool for about 15 to 25 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well, then add coconut and pecans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread jar of Marshmallow Creme on top.
Let cool and ice with Icing.

title: old-fashioned sour cream cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; gradually add eggs and mix well.
Stir in sour cream and add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Chill thoroughly.
Roll out.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake; cookies should not be brown.

title: salmon patties
directions: Flake salmon (do not drain).
Combine all ingredients except margarine and additional crumbs with fork until blended.
Shape into nine 1-inch patties, 1/4 cup each.
Flatten slightly.
Dip in additional crumbs and fry slowly in margarine.
Good with creamed peas spoon over.

title: kidney bean soup deluxe
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Pour off soaking water, then add 5 cups fresh water, bay leaf and Kombu.
Boil until beans are very tender, adding more water as needed.
Saute onion, carrot and apple in oil until tender.
When beans are done, add saute to the pot along with all ingredients except cheese.
Simmer about 10 more minutes; turn off heat and add cheese.
Great with corn bread.

title: chicken stew
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Rinse chicken under cold water; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces; discard bones and skin.
Strain broth and skim off fat.
Return broth to kettle.
Add bouillon.
Stir until dissolved.
Add vegetables; simmer until tender.
Add chicken and simmer 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: best ever brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt together butter and unsweetened chocolate.
To that mixture, add sugar; beat well.
Then add eggs; beat again.
Add flour and beat.
Finally add vanilla and blend well.
Pecans are optional.
Add at the last and mix well.
Bake in an 8 or 9-inch square pan for 25 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Grate cabbage and put in container.
Add salt.
Cover with water and let stand for 2 hours.
Cut up celery and peppers and add to cabbage.
Bring water, vinegar, sugar and celery seed to boil.
Let cool good and then pour over cabbage, celery and pepper.
Mix and put in glass container.
Keeps up to 2 months in refrigerator.

title: snowballs(cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Mix in milk and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts; mix well.
Chill dough thoroughly.

title: oatmeal corn flake cookies
directions: Beat eggs, sugars and oil together.
Sift flour and baking soda and stir in with oil and eggs.
Spoon out with teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: toffee
directions: Melt margarine and add sugar.
Cook over medium-high heat. Bring to rolling boil (mixture will be thick).
Cook until it just begins to turn tan.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan that has been lined with waxed paper.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over toffee and spread out with spatula.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Let cool until hard, then crack to serve.

title: garden frittata omelette
directions: In boiling water, in saucepan, cook potatoes for 5 minutes, until just done.
Drain.
In large nonstick skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute onion for 5 minutes, until soft.
Add all vegetables.
Saute for 6 minutes, until crisp-tender.
Add cheese.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Add coconut and pecans.
Beat until thick.
Great on German Chocolate Cake or Jam Cake.

title: gingerbread with lemon sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9x9x2 baking pan.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, ginger, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder, cloves and salt.
Stir in margarine, water and molasses until well blended.
Pour into pan.
Bake 40-50 minutes until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool slightly on wire rack. Serve warm with Lemon Sauce.
Serves 9-12.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Shape in ball size of walnut; dip in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: jalapeno cheese squares
directions: Whip eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Place chicken breasts in glass dish.
Combine juices, oil and garlic.
Pour over chicken.
Turn to coat all sides.
Marinate 30 minutes or more.
Remove chicken from marinade and season with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Place chicken on greased broiler rack in a foil lined broiler pan so top of chicken is 5 to 7-inches from heat.
Brush marinade every 10 to 15 minutes and turn chicken as it browns.
Broil until done, 30 to 40 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: potato rolls
directions: Let yeast soften in warm water.
Combine fresh mashed potatoes with potato water, sugar, shortening and salt.
When cool, add softened yeast, beaten eggs and 4 cups flour.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Let rest 1/2 hour, then work dough with other flour by hand.
Knead until smooth as satin.
Round in a ball and place in well-greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double. Make into rolls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: quick and easy tex-mex casserole
directions: Place ground chuck, onion, salt and pepper in a large frying pan.
Brown mixture.
When done, add beans, corn, picante sauce and tomatoes; simmer 15 minutes.

title: summer vegetable pasta salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, cheese, parsley and salt.
Mix well. Add noodles and vegetables.
Mix lightly and chill.

title: creamed beef on toast
directions: In 10-inch frypan, combine beef, salt, pepper and onion.
Cook until done.
Drain well.
Return to frypan and add milk.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, stirring as needed to avoid sticking.

title: french dressing chicken
directions: Brush chicken with dressing; add seasoning.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Turn over; brush with dressing.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Simmer onion in butter.
Add mushrooms and bouillon. Make paste from cornstarch and water.
Add to bouillon mixture to thicken.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve hot noodles or rice.

title: cherry dairy dessert
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press all but 1/4 cup in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Melt marshmallows with milk in top of double boiler (or in microwave). Cool.
When cool, fold in whipped cream.
Spread over crumb crust. Spread with cherry pie filling and top with remaining crumbs. Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix salt with cucumbers and onions; let stand for 3 hours. Rinse well.
Make syrup of all other ingredients.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Bring to a scald (do not overcook).
Put in scalded jars and refrigerate.
Enjoy!!!

title: carrot bars
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beef oriental
directions: Cook beef briskly 1 to 2 minutes in 12-inch skillet with salad oil.
Pour soy sauce and water over. Add sugar and monosodium glutamate.
Bring to a boil.
Add celery, onion and green pepper. Cook over high heat for 3 minutes. Add water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Cook until hot. Serves 6.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: granddaddy's fried cornbread
directions: Heat bacon grease in a cast iron skillet.
Mix cornmeal, salt, boiling water to the consistency of oatmeal.
Drop large spoonfuls into hot grease and fry until golden brown and crispy. Serve hot with butter.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients to soft ball stage (234° to 238°) until drops in a cupful of cold water just barely form a ball and will fall apart when removed from the water.
Remove from heat and add the last 3 ingredients. Beat until it begins to thicken and pour into a buttered 9 x 12-inch or 11 x 13-inch pan.

title: mary's chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in small amount of butter.
Mix cheese and soup in pan to melt cheese.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla together.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add sifted ingredients to moist ingredients.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips (optional).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: crunchy cheese crackers
directions: Cream the margarine and cheese.
Add flour and pepper and mix well.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Pinch up small amounts and place on cookie sheet.
Dip a fork in cold water and press down for design. Bake in 325° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fondue cheese
directions: Cook tomato sauce to boil; reduce to simmer.
Toss cheese and flour together and add to sauce when cheese melts.
Gradually add milk and seasoning.
Simmer and stir until smooth!
Cube bread or bread sticks to dip.

title: nut cream drops
directions: Mix sugar, diluted milk and corn syrup.
Boil slowly until a small amount, when dropped in cold water, will form a soft ball. Remove from fire and cool slowly 10 minutes.
Add vanilla and salt.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Add nuts and drop by teaspoon on oiled paper.

title: glazed onions
directions: Prepare and cook onions for 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain well, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
In a medium skillet, combine butter, sugar and reserved liquid.
Cook and stir until combined. Add onions.
Cook, uncovered, over medium-low heat about 15 minutes or until onions are nicely glazed.
Stir often.

title: *yasuko's chicken in wine
directions: Rub each piece of chicken with about 1/2 to 1 teaspoon sugar. Arrange chicken pieces in glass baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour wine over chicken.
(You can adjust amount of wine according to your taste and what you are serving chicken with, to use the juices.)

title: neiman marcus dip
directions: Mix and serve as dip or spread for crackers.

title: bavarian prune plum dumplings
directions: Slit and pit plums.
Place a cube of sugar in center of each plum.
Combine flour, cottage cheese, melted butter, eggs, salt and starch.
Beat until smooth.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Divide dough into 12 portions and wrap around each plum, sealing well.
Cook covered in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Pour melted butter over dumplings or sour cream, if you like it.
Serve hot with roast pork, beef or pot roast.

title: onion cake
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon and discard pan drippings.
In the same skillet, cook onions in butter until tender.
Cool.
In a mixing bowl, combine sour cream, flour and salt; add eggs.
Stir in the bacon and onions; set aside. Separate crescent roll dough into 4 rectangles.
Pat dough into bottom and 1-inch up the sides of a greased 9-inch square baking dish, stretching as needed.
Pinch edges together to seal.
Pour onion mixture over dough.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until topping is set and crust is golden.
Cool slightly before cutting into small squares.
Serve warm.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet until lightly brown.
In a casserole dish, put layer of ground beef, layer of thinly sliced potatoes and layer of onions.
Continue layer of each until all ground beef, potatoes and onions are used.
Top this with the kidney beans and tomato soup.
Cook in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour or until potatoes are tender. Serve with a salad and hot rolls for a delicious meal.

title: christmas egg nog
directions: Beat in 1/3 cup sugar in egg yolks.
Add salt.
Stir in milk, slowly.
Cook over medium heat until it coats a spoon, about 25 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.

title: large banana pudding
directions: Put bananas and wafers in layers.
Combine pudding mix with milk and pour mix over all.
Mix sour cream and Cool Whip together; top pudding with mixture.

title: sherried rice stuffing
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter or margarine.
Add onion and cook until soft and tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Lower heat and simmer, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Let cool before stuffing turkey.

title: nacho dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread cream cheese in baking dish. Add chopped pepper, onion and tomato.
Spread salsa on top, grate cheeses on top.
Bake until bubbles, approximately 20 minutes. Serve hot with chips.

title: louisiana lemon cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Sift soda with flour and add to mixture alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and jello according to package directions.
Do not mix orange juice with 3 cans water.
Combine all 4 ingredients.
Different flavors of Kool-Aid and jello may be substituted.
This makes about 1 gallon of punch.
Add about 1 quart of 7-Up to the punch as you serve.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Mix soup with hamburger and heat. Put hamburger/soup into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add any optional ingredients.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. About 5 minutes before time is complete, sprinkle with cheese; finish baking.

title: raisin-cinnamon rolls
directions: In mixer bowl, combine yeast and 2 1/4 cups of the flour. Heat milk, sugar, shortening and salt until warm; stir until shortening melts.
Add to dry ingredients; add egg.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl. Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in enough of the remaining flour to form soft dough.
Place in greased bowl; turn once. Cover; let rise until double, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: fantasy fudge(no chocolate)
directions: Cook milk, sugar and margarine to soft-ball stage.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla, marshmallow cream and chopped pecans. Return to heat.
Cook to soft-ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Beat by hand for a couple of minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix taco seasoning, corn and beans into beef.
Crumble chips in bottom of long casserole dish (any amount you like).
Pour meat mixture over chips and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top and heat until cheese melts.
Serve with sour cream and mild or hot taco sauce. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin pie(self crust)
directions: Put in bowl or blender for 1 to 2 minutes.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350° in glass pan.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook shells in water only until half done, set aside in a pan of cold water.
Mix the cheeses, eggs and season all salt together.
Stuff shells with cheese mixture, placing them in a lightly greased cake pan.
Pour the spaghetti sauce over shells and bake on 350 degrees for 450 minutes.
Serve when done.
Can also be covered with grated mozzarella cheese.

title: beef stew
directions: Put meat

in crock pot. Mix flour, salt, and pepper; sprinkle over meat. Stir to coat with flour mixture. Add remaining ingredients and stir to mix well. Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or 4 to 6 hours on high.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine all the above ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Mix well.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Divide mixture between the two pans; bake at 325 degrees for one
hour.

title: three pepper shrimp with linguine
directions: Cook pasta until almost al dente.
In a blender, combine chicken broth, peanut butter, sesame oil, soy sauce, vinegar and red pepper. Process until smooth.
Set aside.
Heat olive oil in a large nonstick skillet and saute ginger and garlic 2 minutes.
Add red peppers and shrimp and saute until shrimp is opaque (about 4 minutes).
Stir in chile peppers.
Drain linguine and return to pot.
Stir sauce and add to the pasta; cook until pasta is al dente.
Toss pasta with the shrimp and peppers and top with scallions.
Serves 4.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into balls and brown.
Add to your favorite spaghetti sauce and simmer.
Makes 24 meatballs (1 1/2 pounds meat = 36 meatballs).

title: fluffy buttercream frosting
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in mixture bowl and beat until thick and creamy.
Add milk gradually, a tablespoon at a time.

title: chicken salad amandine
directions: Boil chicken in lightly salted water until meat is tender. Reserve stocks for future use.
Let cool.
Separate meat from bones and skin by pulling.
Leave chicken in medium size strips. Toss remaining ingredients with chicken meat.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Garnish with almonds.

title: beth's candied peanuts
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir until all liquid is gone.
Put on cookie sheet and bake in 250°
oven for 1 hour.

title: celebration punch
directions: In a punch bowl, combine all ingredients.
Garnish with pineapple wedges and lime slices, if desired.
Makes 16 (6 ounce) servings.

title: cocoa-pecan kiss cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine, sugar and vanilla in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Combine flour and cocoa; blend into creamed mixture.
Add pecans; blend on low speed until well blended.
Chill dough 1 hour or until firm enough to handle.

title: cream of chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Separate into small pieces.
Add chicken broth, butter, cream of chicken soup and seasoning salt. Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: bronco buster salad
directions: Fry bacon, set side to cool.
Mix all ingredients, except bacon.
Chill overnight; when ready to serve, add crumbled bacon.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix
cake
mix
and gelatin; add oil, apricot nectar and eggs; beat well.
Cook in tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Ice cake with glaze.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix lightly.
Cover; chill at least 2 hours or up to 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain and bring to room temperature before serving.
Serve with corn chips.

title: buns
directions: Mix yeast and water in a large bowl; add 4 cups flour, oil, eggs, sugar and salt.
Beat with mixer until creamy.
Add rest of flour by mixing with a big spoon.

title: roman holiday
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, drain.
Lightly saute pepper, onion and celery in skillet with ground beef.
Add to this prepared macaroni and cheese and tomatoes.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and top with grated or sliced Cheddar cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until thickened.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add the mayonnaise, cold water and vanilla; beat well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken continental
directions: Roll chicken in flour.
Saute in a little bit of oil.
Mix soup, onion and seasonings in saucepan.
Gradually stir in water. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour Minute rice right from the box into a 9 x 13-inch pan or a 2-quart casserole.
Stir all except 1/3 cup of the soup mixture into rice.
Top with chicken. Pour on remaining soup mixture.
Cover.
Bake for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serves 4.
Bake at 375°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing mix.
Put in bottom of pan.
Mix chicken broth, cream of mushroom soup and cream of chicken soup together.
Pour this over 1/2 of the stuffing mix.
Add small pieces of chicken, then add rest of stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: megan's saturday morning blueberry pancakes
directions: Combine buttermilk, oil and egg; mix with fork.
Add whole wheat flour, white flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix only until moistened.
Fry in hot, lightly greased skillet.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheese and green chili pie
directions: Combine cheeses, eggs and milk.
Line 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish with chilies and cover with the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into bite-size squares and serve.
Cut into larger pieces for a first course or use as a luncheon dish.
Serves 6 to 8. May be frozen and reheated.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together margarine and sugars until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices; add to margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Mix in 1 cup of whipped topping.
Stir in 3/4 cup of the strawberries.
Pour into pie crust, chill until firm, about 15 minutes.
Wisk pudding mix into milk.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups of the whipped topping.
Stir in remaining strawberries. Spread mixture over Jell-O in pie crust.
Chill until set; about 2 hours.
Garnish with additional sliced strawberries.

title: tomato juice
directions: Amount of salt and sugar depends on flavor of tomatoes.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Boil 2 cups water and 1 cup raisins for 5 minutes.
Drain juice off raisins, should be about 1 cup.
Add 1 teaspoon baking soda to juice.
Stir all together.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Cover a baking dish with the raw crescent roll dough; pat until dough is smooth.
Cook dough according to directions on can.
Cool. In mixing bowl, mix mayo and cream cheese.
Add garlic powder and mix.
Spread mixture over cooked crescent roll.
Cook frozen vegetables until crisp-tender.
Put the cooled vegetables on top of the cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle the grated cream cheese over the top.
Decorate top with ripe olive slices.
Refrigerate.
Can be made the night before.

title: mexi-cheese salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine beans, rice, tomato, bell pepper, cilantro and green onions.

title: 7 up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except the 2 egg yolks.
Bake in a 9 x 13 inch pan that was sprayed with Pam.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pear pickle by grandma
directions: Peel pears and cut as for canning.
Place in pot large enough to add sugar and vinegar.
Tie pickle spices in a thin white cloth.
Put in with other ingredients. Cook until syrup turns red. Put in jars and seal while hot.

title: oven-crisp eggplant
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with oregano, paprika and salt.
Set aside. Beat egg with water.
Peel eggplant.
Cut back lengthwise int 6 segments.
Dip eggplants into beaten egg and then into crumb mixture.
Let stand at least 30 minutes.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake in 400° oven for about 20 minutes or until crisp.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine cake mix, 1 stick butter and egg; mix well. Pat into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Beat cream cheese until smooth. Add eggs, vanilla and 1 stick butter; beat until smooth. Add powdered sugar and mix well. Spread over cake mixture. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes. You want the center to be a little gooey, so do not over bake.

title: grandma purcell's rolled oat bread
directions: Add boiling water to oats.
Let stand 1 hour.
Add molasses, brown sugar and butter.
Add dissolved yeast.
Add flour.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Form into loaves, let rise until double again.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: blue banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in bananas and blueberries.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts.
Press into oblong cake pan and bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Let cool and cover with creamed mixture of powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread blueberries next. Then top with Cool Whip.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Mix beans and seasoning.
Spread into bottom of a 9 x 12-inch dish. Layer remaining ingredients.
Serve with chips.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes;
cover	with
water.
Add onion and cook until tender.	Add
margarine and cheese and let them melt. Add parsley and milk; let
simmer
for
a while; do not boil.

title: francis perry's coconut bars
directions: Mix as for pie crust 1 cup flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar and butter.
Spread in a 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Beat together eggs, 1 cup brown sugar, salt, vanilla and 3 tablespoons flour.
Add coconut and pecans.
Spread on top of the crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Cut in bars.

title: colorado chicken salad
directions: Mix first six ingredients together.
Mix mayo with remaining ingredients (except pineapple).
Toss with chicken mixture, chill and serve over pineapple arranged over lettuce leaves.

title: frozen pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for several hours. Serve in a bowl or on lettuce leaves.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Brown meat and drain completely.
Melt Velveeta cheese. Add tomatoes and meat and enough juice from can to dip consistency. Keep hot in
chafing
dish.
Serve	with corn chips or crisp crackers.

title: touchdown cocoa crunch cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 8-inch square baking pan.
In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Beat with a spoon or whisk just until batter is smooth and ingredients are well blended.

title: peanutty chicken salad
directions: Mix together yogurt, peanut butter, milk, vinegar, oil, soy sauce, sugar and spices in a small bowl.
Mix rest of ingredients in bowl.
Add dressing and toss.

title: deluxe cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling, salted water until tender; drain. Combine soup, Worcestershire sauce and pepper in saucepan. Cook until heated through. Spoon over cauliflower and garnish with buttered bread crumbs.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat.
Remove from skillet and pour off fat.
Melt butter and oil in skillet and saute onion and mushrooms in skillet until onion is translucent.
Remove from skillet.
Add flour to skillet and brown.
Add bouillon and blend.
Stir in spices.
Return meat, onion and mushrooms to skillet and simmer all for 15 minutes.
Just before serving, blend in sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles. Serves 6.

title: everlasting slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Chop pepper and onion and mix together.
Boil together vinegar, sugar, salt and spices only until they are well blended.
Pour over slaw and set several hours before serving. Store in refrigerator.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine lemon juice,
jello and hot water.
Chill until begins to set, then add rest of ingredients.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Mix all ingredients together, except for chips and cheese.
Alternate layers with chips, then mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly!

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender before measuring.
Drain off water. Add oleo, salt, pepper and milk.
Mix all together, then add beaten eggs, onion, cheese and cracker crumbs.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake (uncovered) at 375° about 40 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Add brown sugar and margarine.
Mix well, then add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix all dry ingredients together, then add to other mixture.
Add chocolate chips last.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes on a greased and floured cookie sheet.

title: butch's christmas dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: german breaded pork chops
directions: McCormick has a blend of parsley and garlic powder called "Persillade" which ought to be good to use instead of parsley.

title: savory rice blend
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir wild and brown rice, celery and onion in margarine until onion is tender.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat broth to boiling; pour over rice mixture.
Stir in parsley, salt, tamari, sage and basil.
Cook and bake 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; place in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Cook in microwave oven for 10 minutes on 80% power.

title: norwegian strip cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add vanilla; stir in dry ingredients.
Roll out in strips about 3-inches wide and 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in one-inch strips.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake until lightly browned at 375°, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: angel food cake
directions: Add salt to egg whites and beat until frothy.
Add cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in sugar, then vanilla.
Sift in the flour slowly, continuing until all is used.

title: egg and ham casserole
directions: Spread butter on bread and sprinkle with garlic.
Cut into cubes, put into greased baking dish.
Blend rest of the ingredients together.
Pour over bread.
Let stand for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until golden brown.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; add milk if too thick.
Garnish with eggs and paprika, if desired.
Pimentos or red peppers may be cut into strips and placed on top to resemble a poinsetta.

title: no cook noodle lasagne
directions: In saucepan, mix tomatoes, tomato sauce, sauce mix and V-8 juice.
Simmer for several minutes.
In a large pan, place 3 to 4 noodles.
Layer 1/3 meat, 1/3 cottage cheese, 1/3 sauce and 1/3 Mozzarella.
Repeat layers twice.
Sprinkle top layer with Parmesan cheese.
Seal with heavy foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach soup
directions: Cook spinach, then turn into blender with 1/2 to 3/4 cup cooking liquid.
Add broth, onion, butter and flour.
Press #4 and blend 40 seconds.
Press #2; remove cap and pour in milk.
Blend 10 seconds.
Pour mixture into saucepan; simmer over low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in cream and seasonings.
Serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese and add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Add vanilla.
Beat well with mixer. Bake slowly at low heat (from 250° to 300°) for 1 1/2 hours. Bake in tube or large Bundt pan.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse in cold water.
Mix all of the ingredients together.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Optional:
Use fat-free dressing for a fat-free spaghetti salad.

title: hamburgers baked with cream
directions: Combine first six ingredients and form into 8 patties.
Fry patties in skillet until well browned on both sides.
Remove to baking dish.
Drain off excess grease and melt butter in same skillet.
Add onion, carrots and celery to skillet drippings. Saute until tender.
Add flour.
Stir until well blended.
Combine milk and soup and add to vegetables.
Reduce heat and cook until mixture is well blended and thickens.
Pour over hamburgers. Sprinkle with parsley.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Beat together margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add combined flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; mix well. Stir in oats and chocolate chips; mix well. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or golden brown. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder. Beat eggs well. Gradually add sugar and oil, mixing well. Add vanilla and dry ingredients; blend well. Stir in zucchini. Combine walnuts with 1 teaspoon flour. Stir in batter. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until bread tests done. Cool in pans on racks for 10 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Cook at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 300°.
Cook until done, about 20 more minutes. Let cool.
Serve slightly warm or cold.

title: venison ole!
directions: In a crock-pot, combine the cubed beef, enchilada sauce and chili.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts, stirring frequently.

title: chocolate toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into rectangles.
Press into a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Close seams. In a small pan, mix sugar and oleo. Boil 1 minute.
Pour over dough.
Sprinkle with nuts. Bake 14 to 18 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle chocolate bits on top.
Swirl as they melt.
Cut when cool.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Sift flour; measure and resift with remaining dry ingredients. Add gradually to beaten egg, mixing until thoroughly blended. Roll paper thin on floured board, keeping a rectangular shape. Let stand 20 minutes.
Roll in jelly roll style; out 1/8 to 1/2 inch.
Separate and lay flat to dry 2 hours.
Cook until tender in boiling water or soup.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: tuna-fish casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender; blanch in hot water.
Mix in the tuna and the milk with the celery soup.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into baking dish, dot top with butter and bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves. Combine beaten eggs, pumpkin, water and salad oil. Add to dry ingredients. Fold in dates and nuts. Pour into 2 loaf pans. Line pans with paper and spray with Pam. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 2 small loaves.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
In small bowl, stir together eggs, milk, oleo and brown sugar.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until blended.

title: grape salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Congeal.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and sugar together and spread over jello mixture.
Top with 1/2 cup chopped pecans.

title: trail bars
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring until well mixed.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.

title: orange rolls
directions: Mix flour and crisco together and form dough.
Cut out biscuit size pieces.
Roll out flat and spread butter over surface.
Spread marmalade and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Roll up length wise and cut into 3 pieces.
Do this to all biscuits and then place in a greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° until done (about 20 minutes).
When done, pour topping over warm rolls and serve.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter over low heat.
Then add food coloring and vanilla.
Stir in cornflakes.
Form into wreaths on waxed paper and trim with silver shot, red hots or colored sugar. This is good to make in your electric skillet at 150°.

title: homemade ice cream(easy!)
directions: Beat all ingredients together except milk.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Add as much milk as needed to the "fill line" in the ice cream freezer.
Alternate layers of rock salt and crushed ice around the ice cream bucket.
Follow the ice cream freezer manufacturer's directions for freezing.
Enjoy.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse all beans and mix together.
Mix oil, vinegar and sugar and pour over beans and vegetables.
Marinate at least 24 hours.

title: deer stew
directions: Shake deer roast in dry flour. Fry until brown.
Leave oil in pan that you cooked roast in. Cut up onion, potatoes and carrots. Add to roast. Salt and shake black pepper over vegetables. Add water until it completely covers vegetables.
Cook in oven with pan covered 1 hour and 30 minutes. Take out of oven. stir. Add about 1 cup water.
Cook about 30 to 45 minutes or until deer starts separating.
To add flavor, add 1 pack mushroom gravy mix.

title: eggplant crunch
directions: Cook the vegetables in the butter for 15 minutes until soft. Add the tomato sauce, shredded cheese and 1 cup of corn chips. Bake, covered, at 350° in a greased casserole for 25 to 30 minutes (or for 5 to 10 minutes in the microwave).
Uncover.
Top with the remaining 1/2 cup corn chips and bake 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cantaloupe with marsala wine(light dessert, serves about 6)
directions: Clean the stems from the strawberries.
Cut the cantaloupe in half and remove the seeds.
With a melon-ball scooper, scoop out the pulp.
Save the cantaloupe shells.
Place melon balls and strawberries into a large bowl.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and the Marsala wine; mix well.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Sprinkle the cantaloupe shells with the remaining sugar and refrigerate for several hours.
Fill cantaloupe shells with the marinated melon and strawberries.
Spoon some of the juice over the fruit.
Serve chilled.

title: corned beef brisket
directions: Simmer corned beef 1 hour per pound.
Drain water and top with mustard and brown sugar (mixed together).
Cover with aluminum foil; bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Slice and serve.
Can be served with cabbage!

title: playdough
directions: Mix all the food together. Roll it out. Warm in microwave.

title: chocolate graham cracker delight
directions: Finely chop 1/2 package of chocolate.
Heat remaining chocolate and 2 tablespoons of milk in saucepan over low heat. Stir until melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese; add remaining milk and chocolate mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Blend until smooth.
Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle chopped chocolate on top.
Freeze 4 hours.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and bread in large pan or bowl.
Add celery, apples, onions, sage, salt, pepper and 1 raw egg.
Add broth mixed with water (if from turkey or chicken).
Mix until juicy (real juicy).
May need to add canned broth to turkey broth.
Add chopped boiled eggs.
Add melted butter.
Seal in bowl and let set overnight in refrigerator for flavor.
Can add the butter the day of cooking.
Do not cook in deep pan, cook in large baking pan at 400° for 1 hour.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Combine water, bouillon and onion in large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add broccoli and cook until tender (if frozen, cook about 5 minutes).
Put cooked broccoli and onion in food processor and process until finely chopped, but not smooth.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar, blending thoroughly.
Add egg; beat well. Add flour mixture and milk alternately, beating after each addition.
Add nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Drop dough from teaspoon 2 inches apart on well-greased cookie sheet.
Cookies will spread.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Top each cookie with a marshmallow half, cut side down, pushing down a little.
Return to oven; bake 2 minutes longer.
Cool on rack, then frost.
Top with pecan half.

title: cheese rice crispy
directions: Mix cheese and butter.
Add flour and mix well.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Shape into small balls; flatten with fork. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.
Will make about 60.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out about 1/8-inch.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes a tub full.

title: deathly devil's food cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt together.
Blend in oil, water, vinegar and vanilla.
Use a long pan.
Do not grease!
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: berliner ragout
directions: Brown beef in a little oil.
Add onions, garlic, peppers, tomatoes, mushrooms and parsley.
Simmer until almost complete. Add A.1. sauce and the cognac and cook for 1 minute.
Goes very well with fried potatoes.
Serves 6.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Combine shortening and sugar, salt with starter.
Stir to combine.
Place 4 cups flour in large bowl.
Make depression in center, pour in batter, cut flour into batter until you have ball that can be handled.
Place on well-floured board and knead remaining flour into ball until smooth and elastic (about 20 minutes).
Grease top and set aside for 8 hours.

title: dip meatballs
directions: Shape into balls; brown in skillet, dip in sauce of choice.

title: ribbon cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Gradually add flour, baking powder and salt.

title: meringue
directions: Mix all ingredients until it peaks.
Put on pie.
Bake until brown.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Combine Ranch mix and oil. Add lemon pepper, garlic powder and dill weed.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix butter and eggs.
Add sugar.
Stir in flour and milk.
Add vanilla and chopped pecans.
Bake in two 9-inch pie shells for about 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: ooey gooey pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips.
Add sugar and eggs.
Stir well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt.
Beat together the remaining ingredients.
Mix in flour.
Roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press each with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Boil water with margarine.
Add flour and stir until it leaves side of pan.
Add eggs and beat.
Spread this mixture into a greased jelly roll pan and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool.

title: easy taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients in bowl and serve.
May be served in Aztec salad shells.

title: boiled custard
directions: Over low heat, stir constantly until thick but do not boil. Add 1/2 teaspoon lemon extract and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.

title: dirty rice
directions: Boil bell pepper, onion and celery until done.	Reserve liquid to cook rice for more flavor.
Brown ground chuck and sausage and drain.	Mix with rice mixture and add mushrooms. Serve hot with margarine and cheese if desired.
Serves 6.

title: dutch hot slaw
directions: Cook cabbage and drain. Keep hot.
Melt margarine in double boiler.
Add remaining ingredients except cream.
Cook, stirring until thickened. Remove from heat.
Add cream.
Beat until smooth. Pour over cabbage.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix well the margarine, peanut butter, powdered sugar and Rice Krispies.
Will have to do the mixing with hands. Form all mixture into walnut size balls.
Place on wax paper lined counter or cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips with paraffin (melts easier if shaved).
Dip balls, one at a time, in chocolate mixture and place on waxed paper to set.
Makes approximately 80 balls.

title: jean's blue ribbon chili
directions: This can be decreased to any size.
I like to make a large pot and freeze some for later.
In large pot of water, boil meat and onion until meat is done.
Crumble and drain
Add kidney beans bell pepper, special sauce chili seasoning and 2 cups water. Simmer for 2-3 hours uncovered, stirring occasionally.
(May need to add more water as it simmers if becomes too thick.)

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook vegetables all together in oleo until tender.
Prepare Stove Top dressing according to package directions.
Add dressing, mushroom soup and milk to vegetables.
Grease baking dish.
Layer 1/2 dressing, 1/2 cheese, other 1/2 dressing and ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
This makes a very large casserole.

title: creamy cheesecake pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and the margarine.
Press in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.
Heat oven to 300°.
Beat cream cheese in large mixer bowl.
Add 1 cup sugar gradually, beating until fluffy.
Add lemon peel and vanilla.
Beat in 1 egg at a time. Pour over crumb mixture.
Bake about 1 hour; cool.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours and top with glaze.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix the vanilla wafer crumbs and margarine.
Mix together soft cream cheese, sugar, milk and Dream Whip; fold in pecans and set aside.
In baking dish, make a layer of crumbs and a layer of whipped cream mixture (1/2).
Pour can of cherry pie filling and rest of white mixture.
Add remainder of vanilla wafer crumbs and garnish with maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate about 12 hours before serving.

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Cream softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; whip cream. Fold into cheese mixture; mix lemon juice in blueberry pie filling.
Mix 1/2 cream cheese mixture into blueberries; put in pastry shell.
Spread remaining cream on top.
Chill.

title: easy fruit torte
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in an 8-inch square pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Best served the next day.
Top with Cool Whip.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hallelujah squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain and mash. Add slightly beaten eggs, soup, margarine and 1/2 to 3/4 crushed crackers.
Mix well.
Sprinkle remaining crackers mixed with a little butter on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Amen!

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk and cocoa for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: mom's homemade chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken, basil, garlic, celery seed and diced onions in 8 pints of water for about 30 to 45 minutes or until tender.
After chicken is cooked, remove from pot and set out to cool.
Add frozen vegetables and sliced carrots.
Boil for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to warm.
Remove meat from chicken carcass.
Break up or cut up meat into bite size portions.
Add to vegetables and broth.
Add egg noodles.
Leave pot on warm until noodles become soft.
Stir frequently.
Enjoy!

title: crisscross cranberry pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add water and heat until sugar is melted.
Add cranberries.
Cook slowly until all the skins pop open.
Add lemon and butter.
Cool, but do not stir.
Pour into pastry lined 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with crisscross pastry strips.
Brush top with milk.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 30 minutes.

title: spiced almond macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets well.
Mix sugar, almonds and cinnamon.
Beat egg whites in a medium-size bowl with electric mixer until stiff but not until dry peaks form when beaters are lifted.
Gently stir (fold) in ground cinnamon-almond mixture.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on prepared cookie sheet.
Sprinkle a sliced almond or two on top of each. Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool about 2 minutes before remove to wire rack to cool completely.
(If the last few stick, return cookie sheet to oven to reheat and remove cookies immediately.)
Makes 24.

title: crazy cake 2
directions: Bring to a boil the first 3 ingredients and pour over flour and sugar.
Mix.
Then add buttermilk, soda, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Mix and pour into well-greased and floured pan.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: almond bars
directions: Mix oleo, paste, sugar and eggs in that order.
Add flour last.
Put (pat) into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Boil sugar and butter 3 minutes; don't overcook.
Line 11 x 15-inch sheet pan with crackers.
Pour sugar mixture over the crackers.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes only.
Cut and put on wax paper.

title: summer silk pie
directions: Make pudding as directed on package, but using
only 1 1/2 cups milk.
Melt chocolate squares and blend into pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into pie crust.
Freezes in 2 to 3 hours. Slightly thaw to serve.
Add chocolate shavings for decoration.

title: chocolate fondant
directions: Mix ingredients together. Roll into balls or spoon dip. Put in freezer to get firm.

title: quick and easy corn relish
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Heat just until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from the heat and refrigerate.

title: fruit compote
directions: Combine fruits.
When sauce has cooled, pour over fruit and serve, garnished with sprig of mint, if desired.

title: old-fashioned lemonade
directions: Combine water, lemon juice and sugar in serving container. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add ice cubes.
Garnish with mint leaves and orange or lemon slices.

title: ruby's bean dip
directions: Brown the meat with the onions.
Add all other ingredients, except the shredded cheese,
and
mix
well.
Place in a baking dish; sprinkle the shredded
cheese on top.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: elephant ears(welcome school's)
directions: Pat the biscuit flat.
Cut in half.
Dip or brush each half with butter.
Then sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Combine marshmallows, Hershey bars and milk in top of double boiler.
Heat until melted; cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour in baked pie crust and chill at least 2 hours.
(Double recipe and put in 13 x 9-inch pan for large desserts.)

title: honey carrots
directions: Cook carrots; drain.
Reserve 1/4 cup carrot liquid.
Combine liquid, honey, oleo and brown sugar.
Stir well and pour over carrots.
Cook over low heat.
Serves 6.

title: pink fluff salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: cheese balls
directions: Have oleo at room temperature.
Mix in cheese.
Add pepper, salt and flour to which baking powder has been added.
Work together well until mixture is formed into dough.
Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 400° until slightly brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute 1 stick of oleo and onion until onion is tender.
Place cream of chicken soup, Minute rice, Velveeta cheese and broccoli in a greased casserole.
Add onion.
Pour 1 stick melted oleo over Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese on toast
directions: Plug toaster in.
Remove bread from package.
Place bread in toaster and start toaster.
When toast pops up, place on plate and put cheese on toast.
Close bread wrapper, unplug toaster and eat. For a change, microwave sandwich to melt cheese.

title: mushroom-currant jelly chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Spray ovenproof dish with oil and add chicken to pan.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.
Cover chicken with mixture of heated jelly, sherry and sauteed mushrooms and bake 1 hour more, uncovered.

title: reception salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
In 1/4 of this liquid, soak the Knox gelatine for 5 minutes.
Heat remaining liquid; add gelatine, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Stir well.
Put in refrigerator until it begins to jell.
With mixer, beat cream cheese until it is creamy; mix in pineapple, celery and gelatine mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in mold or flat dish.
Refrigerate until set up.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in
boiling
water;
add
sliced
strawberries, while hot, and undrained pineapple.
Pour about 1 1/2 cups	of jello mixture
into
mold.	Let
chill
until
firm. Spread half of sour
cream over firm jello.
Spread more jello and chill again.
Spread rest of sour cream and rest of jello. Chill overnight.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk; add vanilla and food coloring.
Mix vinegar and soda; add last.
Bake in two 9-inch layers at 325°, which are to be split crosswise with a thread to make 4 layers, or one large sheet which can be cut into 4 parts.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and sausage. Add onion, celery, bell pepper, Rotel and chili powder. Add cabbage, water and raw rice. Mix well and cook a few minutes. Put in covered dish; add cheese sauce. Bake at 400 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: weight watchers stir and drop cookies
directions: Beat eggs; stir in oil.
Add vanilla; blend in sugar.
In a different bowl, blend flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients with egg mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Each cookie has 40 calories.

title: cream cheese pineapple biscuits
directions: Press fingers into center of each biscuit, making a deep indention and 1 3/4-inches wide.
Fill indentions with cream cheese.
Arrange pineapple around outside edge of cream cheese. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake as directed on biscuit package.

title: caraway-cheese french bread
directions: Combine cheese, caraway seed and mayonnaise.
Cut 1-pound loaf bread diagonally almost through to bottom crust, into 1-inch slices.
Spread butter or margarine between slices.
Spread cheese mixture between each slice of bread.
Wrap loaf in aluminum foil. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken gumbo soup
directions: Cut up chicken and place in kettle with water, 1 onion, celery, salt, carrot, pepper, bay leaf, thyme and cayenne.
Bring to boil; turn heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Cool, remove chicken from broth and strip meat from bones.
Skim excess fat from broth and strain, if wished.
Heat butter, add remaining onion, garlic and parsley. Cook until tender, but not brown.
Add broth and rice; simmer for 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add chicken, tomatoes and okra.
Cook for 10 minutes or until okra is tender.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix bananas, egg, sugar and shortening.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nutmeats and pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: supper skillet("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Use your imagination!
These are basic ingredients with approximate amounts.

title: bunny salads
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Fill each pear half with a mixture of cottage cheese, mayonnaise and chopped almonds.
Place on bed of lettuce and shredded gelatin (made by forcing firm gelatin through a ricer).
Make bunny's ears, mouth and tail with almonds.
Make eyes by dipping knife end into paprika.
Garnish with small carrot shaped from cheese and sprig of parsley.
Serve with mayonnaise. Makes 6.

title: mint mold candy
directions: Mash cream cheese. Add peppermint and mix well. Add food coloring at this time also. Add sugar and knead until consistency of pie dough. Roll into marbles. Coat with granulated sugar. Press into candy mold; unmold at once. Let dry. Can freeze or store in covered containers.

title: sourdough pancakes
directions: Mix together flour, water and starter.
Cover and let stand overnight in a warm place.
In the morning take out 1/2 to 1 cup and put back with your jar of starter.
Add remaining ingredients and let set 15 minutes to start rising again.
Pour on hot greased griddle.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cut margarine and Velveeta into small pieces.
Mix spinach, cottage cheese, margarine, Velveeta and flour.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Chop tomato, onion, garlic and peppers in food processor.
Add with cream cheese to boiler.
Cook over low heat until melted, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: cherry square
directions: Cream sugar, salt and margarine.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and vanilla.
Spread 1/2 of batter on greased cookie sheet and top with 1/2 the fruit.
Spread rest of batter and then rest of fruit.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Very good!

title: shrimp salad
directions: Make macaroni according to directions on box.
Drain shrimp, peas and pineapple.
Mix all together.
Add Miracle Whip to taste. Season with Lawry's seasoned salt, onion salt and garlic salt.

title: mom's irish soda bread
directions: Add all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Blend in margarine with pastry blender.
Add egg, milk, sour cream and raisins and knead with hands.
Form a ball.
Place in dry layer cake pan and flatten slightly.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: low-fat cheese and vegetable chowder
directions: In a 4-quart pan, combine the vegetables and the dry potatoes with sauce mix.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Combine the milk and cornstarch; add to soup.
Simmer, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes more or until potatoes are tender.

title: kit kat bars
directions: Place layer of crackers in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt margarine and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bring to a boil; boil for 5 minutes, stirring almost constantly.
Spread half of mixture over crackers.
Place another layer of crackers over this and spread remaining mixture on top.
Top with third layer of crackers; frost.

title: simple chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Sprinkle seasoning and garlic powder over top.
Add whole mushrooms and chopped green onions.
Pour wine over top.
Cover dish and bake for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: michele's clam dip
directions: Melt cream cheese and Old English cheese in a pot. Chop pepper and scallions. Add to pot.
Add clams and Worcestershire sauce. Serve hot with bugles.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Scald milk.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and cardamon.
Add milk and cooked rice.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Place in shallow pan of water and bake at 350°.
After 20 to 25 minutes of baking, insert a fork and stir from sides without disturbing the top.
Dot with melted butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Continue baking 35 minutes, more or less, until custard is set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dark chocolate fudge
directions: Line a 9-inch square pan with aluminum foil.
In a heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk and salt, stirring often.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly in pan and cool.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour cans of pineapple and cherry pie filling into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour dry cake mix over top.
Slice butter over cake mix.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pork chops and broccoli
directions: Trim excess fat from the pork chops.
Rub with crushed garlic and set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a heavy skillet.
Add chops to the hot oil.
Brown each side.
Lower heat and cover. Cook chops slowly until done (about 25 minutes).
Turn once. Season and remove the chops.
Pour any pan juices over the chops.

title: cauliflower
directions: Remove core and break cauliflower into flowerettes.
Brown in olive oil for 2 minutes, stirring.
Add water, cover and cook for 8 minutes over medium heat.
