title: microwave broccoli and cheese
directions: Place broccoli on microwave dish with flowerets toward outside of dish.
Cover with plastic wrap tightly.
Cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Pour cheese sauce over broccoli while hot.

title: creamed tuna on toast
directions: Open soup; put in large pan.
Open peas and tuna and add to soup.
Add salt, pepper, butter, Miracle Whip and milk.
Stir well.
Heat thoroughly until hot and creamy.
Serve over toast.

title: lake buena vista strawberry soup
directions: Mix in blender at low speed until thoroughly mixed.
Chill and serve with fresh strawberry garnish.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes.
Place in casserole dish.
Put oleo on potatoes and bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper and cheese.
Bake another 20 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Place in greased baking dish.
Layer cubed chicken.
Combine chicken soup, mayo, lemon juice and sherry.
Pour over chicken.
Top with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Drizzle over top melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken in crock-pot
directions: Place potatoes in bottom of crock-pot.
Layer chicken breasts on top.
Mix celery soup with water. Pour over potatoes and chicken in crock-pot.
Cook on high 8 hours.
Last 15 minutes, add frozen peas.

title: mother's sugar cookies
directions: Roll out and cut.
Bake in a quick oven.
Makes 60 to 75 cookies.

title: wild rice and meatball casserole
directions: Measure wild rice (uncooked).
Prepare according to package directions; set aside.
Combine bread crumbs, milk, salt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Let stand a few minutes.
Add meat and mix well.
Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Make meatballs and brown on all sides in hot oil.
Remove browned meat from pan.
Add celery and onions to drippings and brown lightly.
Add soup, water, wine, pimentos and olives.
Stir in cooked rice.
Fold in meatballs.

title: chicken salad
directions: Lightly mix the first 10 ingredients together.
Moisten with mayonnaise, using more or less as desired.
Mound in 4 decorative serving dishes; sprinkle the minced green chiles and minced sun-dried tomatoes on top.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with corn chips or crisp-fried tortillas as a light lunch.
Yield:
4 servings.
Carbohydrate 6 g, protein 29 g, fat 25 g, calories 365.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine thawed Cool Whip, milk, cherry pie filling and pineapple chunks.
Spoon into paper lined muffins and freeze.

title: wild blackberry cobbler
directions: Heat blackberries with 1/2 cup sugar and butter in large saucepan just until sugar dissolves and butter melts.
Mix remaining sugar with flour.
Stir in the milk and eggs and combine the rest of the ingredients, mixing well.
Pour this batter into buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon blackberry mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool before serving. Very good with trickle of heavy cream served on top.

title: monte carlo sandwiches
directions: On each of four bread slices, place 1 slice each of ham, turkey and cheese.
Cover with remaining slices of bread.
In a bowl, beat eggs, milk, and salt together.
Dip each sandwich carefully into egg mixture, turning to dip each side.
Fry in sprayed or oiled pan like you would French toast, making sure cheese is melted and meat is hot.
May be put on sprayed cookie sheet; bake at 375 degrees, turning once.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown hamburger, garlic powder and onion.
Cool, then add oregano, tomato soup, salad oil and grated Mozzarella cheese. Stir together and simmer a few minutes.
Spread mixture on split hamburger buns.
Cover with Cheddar cheese (shredded) and broil for 3 to 5 minutes, until cheese bubbles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mustard-fried catfish
directions: Pat fish dry.
In large skillet, over medium-high heat, bring 1-inch oil to 350°.

title: dana's pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add brown sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cut oven off and let sit for 25 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: seven step jerky
directions: Note:
Leftovers are generally used for jerky; strips off the ribs, neck and trimmings from lower hams and shoulders.

title: heath bar candy
directions: Cook sugar, almonds, and butter.
Stir until it is the color of creamed coffee.
Watch carefully.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch butter dish.
Place 5 Hershey candy bars over top of this.
Heat from cooked mixture will melt chocolate.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle pecan meal on top.
Score and put in refrigerator.
When cool, cut or break where scored.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in sliced squash, crumbled muffins, onion and top with cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Beat together the sour cream, flour, salt, vanilla, egg and diced apples.
Put into 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Mix flour, brown sugar and butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake 20 minutes longer.

title: quickie blueberry dessert
directions: Bring to a rolling boil the blueberries, water, lemon juice and 1/4 cup sugar.
Mix flour, oil, cinnamon, 1/4 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons water until well mixed.
Drop by spoonful into boiling blueberries.
Cover and cook over medium heat about 10 minutes or until dumplings are done.
Serves 4 to 6. May serve with whipped topping or vanilla ice cream.
Serve warm.

title: french silk pie
directions: Beat sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla, cream of tartar and chocolate.
Beat in eggs until light and fluffy.
Pour into shell.
Refrigerate until set, 3 to 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip to serve.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Dream Whip and 1 cup sugar together and spread on top of cooked pretzel base. Dissolve jello in water.
Drop in frozen strawberries when jello is slightly thickened.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Sprinkle crushed pretzels over top.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Mix all together; put in a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion. celery, parsley, pepper and mushrooms (if using fresh ones saute).

title: crab or shrimp pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread on platter.
Top with 3/4 bottle chili sauce, crab or shrimp, chopped onion and sprinkle with basil and parsley flakes.
Make 24 hours in advance.
Serve with crackers (saltines or Ritz.)

title: mexican chicken
directions: Grease large casserole.
Cover bottom with Doritos, which have been dipped in chicken stock.
Put layer of bite size chicken chunks.
Add onion and bell pepper; cover with grated cheese.
Add chili powder and garlic powder.
Pour on soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Top with more cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal, flour and onion; add egg.
Gradually beat in milk or water.
Drop from spoon into hot fat.
Fry until golden brown, turning.
Makes about 16 small hush puppies.

title: molasses gingerbread cookies
directions: Mix ingredients, except the flour.
Mix enough flour in to make easy to roll out.
Roll out.
Cut and bake on greased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: italian meatball soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine undrained tomatoes, beef broth, water, and Italian seasoning and bring to boiling.
Stir in meatballs, frozen vegetables, and pasta.
Return to boiling, reduce heat.
Simmer covered for about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Ladle soup into serving bowls and top with parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tostado bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Cook and stir ground beef until brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato sauce and beans.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Pour salad dressing over hot potatoes.
Stir to partially mash potatoes.
Add finely chopped egg whites.
Sieve egg yolks and mix with mayonnaise, sour cream and mustard. Stir into potatoes.
Add onions.
Salt as desired. Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked onion casserole
directions: Layer onions, crushed potato chips and cheese.
Make at least 2 layers.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add baking powder to flour and then alternately add flour and milk.
Always end with some flour.
Stir in flavoring.
Turn oven on just before putting batter into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: doc's favorite squash casserole
directions: Mix together squash, soup, butter, crackers, salt, pepper and cubed cheese.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in microwave for 4 minutes or until cheese melts.
Top with remaining cheese, place back in the microwave for 2 minutes.

title: pumpkin  harvest loaf
directions: Grease bottom of a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Sift dry ingredients. Alternate with pumpkin.
Stir in chips and nuts after adding butter and eggs.
Pour into pan sprinkled with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes.
Cool and drizzle glaze over top.
Let stand at least 6 hours before serving.

title: bacon and egg potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine potatoes and onions.
In a small saucepan, combine lemon juice, water, oil, celery salt, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over potato mixture; mix well.
Cover; chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator for 30 minutes before serving.
Stir in bacon, eggs, cheese and parsley.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend sugar, eggs, vanilla and oil.
Use electric mixer for this, but stir in chopped apples by hand.
Sift dry ingredients together; blend into sugar mixture.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour, or until done, at 350°.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix together.
Place in greased muffin pan.
Fill half full. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Mix cake mix (save back 2/3 cup of this), egg and melted oleo. Spray bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Add mixture and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
While this is cooking, mix:

title: six weeks bran muffins
directions: Pour
boiling
water
over 2 cups bran; let stand while assembling other ingredients.
Mix in shortening.
Mix rest of bran
with	sugar,	eggs and buttermilk.
Sift flour with salt and soda.
Combine all ingredients and bake as many as needed, at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs. Gradually add sugar to eggs and continue to beat until mixture is very stiff.
Add Milnot, vanilla and salt; mix thoroughly.
Pour into a gallon freezer and fill to fill line with milk.
Stir and freeze as directed.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Brown meats and drain well.
Melt cheese and Ro-Tel together. Add all ingredients together, adding jalapeno peppers to taste. Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak and onion in oleo.
Stir in mushroom soup, water, sour cream and paprika.
Cover; cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Serve over cooked egg noodles.

title: quick vegetable-beef soup
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Add tomato sauce and onion.
Crumble in uncooked beef.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes to an hour, adding water as needed.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar before serving.

title: frying pan cookies
directions: Heat sugar, dates and eggs in frying pan and stir until mixture is brown and comes away from the pan.
Remove from stove and add salt, vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonfuls into coconut or nutmeats and roll.

title: royal seafood casserole
directions: Blend soup into mayonnaise in a large bowl.
Stir until smooth. Add onion, then milk.
Now begin seasoning.
Use a heavy hand because rice and seafood are bland.
When mixture is well seasoned, combine with other ingredients except paprika and almonds.
Check seasonings; add a few tablespoons milk if mixture is dry.
It should be moist.
Turn into large shallow buttered casserole. Sprinkle with paprika and scatter almonds over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Freezes well.
Yields 10 servings.

title: pasta e ceci(pasta and chickpeas)
directions: Put oil and onion in large saucepan.
Turn heat to medium. When onion becomes colored pale, add garlic, rosemary and sage. Stir once or twice.
When garlic becomes very pale, add tomatoes. Cook, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes.
Add chickpeas and cook another 5 to 6 minutes.

title: hermits
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add egg.
Beat, then add dry sifted ingredients.
Add milk and fold in raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased pan.
Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes.

title: strawberry and peach pie
directions: Combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Blend until mixed.
Pour over strawberries and peaches.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Make crust out of biscuit dough.
Roll out dough the size of pan.
Put over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peachy carrots
directions: Combine carrots with margarine and peach preserves.
Cook over low heat until carrots are heated thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
This can be mixed in food processor for creamier texture.

title: hamburger biscuit cups
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add barbecue sauce and simmer until done.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs and mix in sugar, oil, vanilla, zucchini and pineapple. Sift dry ingredients together and mix thoroughly with zucchini mixture. Add raisins and nuts and mix well. Pour batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Put in cold oven and turn to 325°. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour or until bread tests done with toothpick. Cool in pans. (Can use frozen zucchini. Can vary nuts and fruits. Also can pour batter into 4 small oiled and floured loaf pans and bake 40 to 45 minutes.)

title: chicken in wine
directions: Salt and pepper chicken breast halves, then brown in margarine.
Remove to large, shallow casserole.
To the same skillet that chicken was browned in, add soup, sour cream and wine.
Mix well and pour over chicken in casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Serve with rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into patties.
Fry in hot oil until nice and brown.

title: black-eyed pea soup
directions: Clean and drain black-eyed peas.
Set aside.

title: grilled zucchini
directions: Brush the zucchini with olive oil and arrange the zucchini slices in a baking pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella, salt, pepper and oregano.
Broil for about 5 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican chef's salad
directions: Chop onion, tomatoes and lettuce.
Toss with grated cheese and dressing.
Add hot sauce, if desired.
Slice and add avocado. Brown beef, kidney beans and salt; simmer 10 minutes.
Add to cold salad.
Crunch tortilla chips and add.
Garnish with chips, avocado and tomato slices. Serve pronto!

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and shortening together on low speed about 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
Sift together and add plain flour, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Do not open oven.

title: cole slaw to can
directions: Mix all ingredients and
let
set awhile.
Pack in jars so juice is on top.
Cold pack 10 minutes.
Makes 5 pints.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Thoroughly cream together the sugar, vanilla and shortening. Beat in eggs and melted chocolate.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add alternately with milk.
Add walnuts.
Chill 3 hours.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar. Place on greased cookie sheet 2 to 3-inches apart.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 48.

title: frozen congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Cut up bananas in pineapple juice.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to cranberry sauce.
Mix and add pineapple and bananas. Discard pineapple juice.
Add nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix well and pour into casserole dish and freeze.
Make a day ahead.
Take out of freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: onion ring batter
directions: Drop battered onion rings into deep fat and fry until golden brown. Slice onion beforehand and sprinkle with salt.

title: rice krispies turtles
directions: Melt chips and butter in microwave until melted.
Add marshmallows and melt.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and cool.

title: nestle original toll house cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
Combine butter or margarine, brown sugar, water, granulated sugar, vanilla and sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in real semi-sweet chocolate chips and chopped nuts (optional).
Drop by well rounded half-teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 100 (2-inch) cookies.

title: old-fashioned vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except frozen vegetables and macaroni in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Add frozen vegetables and return to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Stir in macaroni and continue to cook for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chocolate over hot, but not boiling, water. Add other ingredients and mix well. Drop on buttered sheet by spoonfuls and chill until firm. Serves 24.

title: super duper potatoes
directions: Boil the potatoes with skins on; let sit for 48 hours in refrigerator.
Shred the potatoes.
Add grated cheese in layers. Pour melted oleo, salt and evaporated milk over all.
Save a little cheese for the top.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, uncovered, in a greased glass 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish at 350°.

title: quick veggie stew
directions: Turn medium heat on under large pot with your favorite sugarless sauce in it and leave on as you cut and add next 5 ingredients (should take about 5 minutes).
When all vegetables are added, cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes, until sauce begins to boil.
Gently stir in grated cheese or sprinkle on surface of vegetables.
Cover and cook just until cheese melts.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut into thin slices, not all the way through. Place in dish that is microwave-safe.
Sprinkle with melted butter and herbs. Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Rearrange potatoes after 5 minutes.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheeses and microwave 4 to 6 minutes at High until cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft.
Serve.

title: california dip
directions: Mix well; chill 2 hours.
Makes 2 to 3 cups.

title: broccoli chicken bake
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Mix soup and sour cream in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in all except French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with French fried onions.
Bake 5 to 8 more minutes.
Serve.
Tastes great!!

title: fried pies(pear)
directions: Peel pears and add the amount of sugar you want.
Cook down; drain juice.
Add flour and cinnamon.
Thicken; cook slow until desired thickness.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Cut dried beef in small pieces, mix with cream cheese, olives, horseradish and Parmesan (if desired).
Form into a log or ball.
Refrigerate.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: doris' pink punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large container.
Freeze 1 gallon for ice.
Chill all other.
Serve with ice cream (optional).

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Add spinach and bacon bits.
Spread thinly on tortillas and roll up tightly.
Chill for about 2 hours or longer.
Slice and serve.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon
until crisp.
Remove bacon and saute onion for 1 minute. Blend in rest of ingredients.
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: bunuelos
directions: Combine flour, 4 teaspoons sugar, baking powder and salt. Combine eggs and milk, beating well.
Add egg liquid to dry ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Place dough on floured surface and knead, adding flour until very smooth.
Divide into 16 balls, place in bowl, cover with towel and let stand for 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine 1 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Roll balls to paper thickness, retain circle shape.
Carefully fry circles, one at a time, in medium hot oil, until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Immediately sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Yield: 1 1/4 dozen.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, salt and butter.
Beat eggs, lemon rind and vanilla into creamed mixture until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Gradually stir into creamed ingredients.

title: potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Combine hamburger, onion, soup, water and cheese; heat in skillet until cheese has melted.

title: coffee bars
directions: Mix dry ingredients; set aside.
Beat eggs; add brown sugar and coffee.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add vanilla and oil. Mix.

title: hot sweet cabbage
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and fry, but not too brown.
Add cabbage and celery; turn frequently just enough to absorb fat, not too brown.

title: basic egg pie
directions: Mix and pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter 'n chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat butter, sugars and peanut butter in a large bowl with mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy. Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes.
Remove. Yields 4 dozen.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar, food coloring and cornstarch together and cook until thick and clear.
Add 4 tablespoons of Jell-O (dry) and cool.
Mix with strawberries and put into pie shell.
Refrigerate and top with whipped cream when ready to serve.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and salt gradually.
Stir in vanilla and crushed pineapple.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour or until done at 350°.
Spread glaze over warm cake.

title: cheesy sausage balls
directions: Cook onion and sausage together, then drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls and place on a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 425°
for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Blend the margarine, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to the creamed mixture.
Stir in the chopped pecans, dates and 1/3 cup chopped cherries.
Grease a baking sheet and drop cookie batter from a teaspoon, about one-half full.
Place a piece of cherry (1/2 or 1/3) in the center of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: easy summer salad
directions: Step 1:
If desired, precook carrots, cauliflower and onions for 1 minute in boiling water.
Drain.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Combine egg, milk and oil; add all at once to flour mixture; stir just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries. Lightly grease muffin cups or line with paper cups for baking. Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix instant vanilla pudding and 2 cups milk.
Beat well.
Stir in 1 (8 ounce) container of Cool Whip and 1 (8 ounce) container of sour cream.
Stir in four large sliced bananas.
Layer with vanilla wafers.
Top with 8 ounce container of Cool Whip.
Chill for at least 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom of 12 muffin cups.
Mix all ingredients just until flour is moist.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon sugar over each muffin.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.

title: sliced sweet potato casserole
directions: Layer sliced potatoes in baking dish. Mix all ingredients together and pour over potatoes. Place in oven until ingredients are melted and warm.

title: angel hair tomato basil toss
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add garlic and onions. Stir-fry for one minute.
Stir in tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring frequently.
Prepare angel hair according to directions.
Drain.
Toss tomato mixture with hot cooked angel hair.
Serve immediately.
Sprinkle cheese into mixture.
Save some for top.
Refrigerate.
Good also cold.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Beat together pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers, sides with one-quarter piece of cracker.
Put half of pudding on top of crackers.
Cover with crackers.
Spread chocolate frosting on top.
Refrigerate about 24 hours.

title: beef stick
directions: Mix together with hands and let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Divide into 4 equal parts and roll into log, working out air pockets.
Wrap each log in 15-inch square cheesecloth and bake on oven racks with drip pan under for 4 hours at 225°.

title: bean casserole
directions: Mix all beans together and cook on low heat for 1 hour. Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients, except onion, and pour over bean mixture.
Heat until it bubbles.
Cover with onion rings and brown in 350° oven.

title: ice cream cake(make night before serving)
directions: Melt margarine and add brown sugar.
Stir until well mixed. Add one egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, baking powder and salt, then mix in vanilla and chocolate bits.
Pour into greased pan, about 10-inch.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Toss apples with lemon juice, sugar and 2 tablespoons real mayonnaise. Chill.
Combine with remaining ingredients just before serving.

title: garden spiral salad
directions: Cook garden spirals in 4 quarts of water until tender.
Drain and rinse with cold water to cool.
Combine with the remaining ingredients and chill.

title: sweet-n-sour meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, salt, pepper and diced onion.
Make into meatballs.
Brown meatballs, then set aside in bowl.
While pan is still hot, add the sauce.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Soak nuts in vinegar.
Mix together sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla. Then add coconut, raisins and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
(Do not overbake.)

title: chocolate chip-rice krispies cookies
directions: Cream margarine and oil; gradually add sugars, beating at medium speed.
Add egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar; add to creamed mixture gradually.
Stir in oats and remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes (350° for 12 minutes on my stove).
Cool on wire racks.
Yields 10 dozen cookies.

title: plantation barbecue sauce
directions: Combine; simmer 15 minutes.
Use as basting sauce for poultry, beef, spareribs and hot dogs.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: e. f.'s miracle soup
directions: Cut all vegetables in small pieces.
Place in crock-pot and cover with water.
Add 1 package of dry soup mix for seasoning. Let cook on low all day (6 to 8 hours), depending on desired texture of vegetables.

title: rice pudding
directions: Heat milk
in
top of double boiler.
Add rice and cook over water
until
rice	gets
soft.
Add
sugar
and salt and continue cooking until thick.
Add some of the rice to the egg yolks and beat
with fork in a small bowl, then add to the hot mixture in double boiler.
Stir in vanilla.
Remove from heat and pour into bowl.
Cool.

title: slovakian cabbage soup
directions: Combine beef bones, onion, carrots, garlic and bay leaf in roasting pan.
Top with short ribs; sprinkle with thyme and paprika.
Roast, uncovered, in 450° oven for 25 minutes or until meat is brown.
Transfer into a kettle scraping meat from roaster; add remaining ingredients.
Cover with 8 to 10 cups water; boil. Cover; simmer 1/2 hour.
Remove bones; cut meat in cubes.
Return to kettle.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk.
Work together until well moistened.
Cover bowl. Store in refrigerator.
When ready to use, take out amount desired.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out.
Bake 12 minutes at 400°.
Makes 6 dozen.
Will keep several weeks.

title: fudge squares
directions: Mix butter, sugar, salt, eggs, flour and vanilla.
Pour into 2 greased and floured pans.
Cook at 200° for 30 minutes.
Press in pecans and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Cool partially.
Cut into squares.

title: cheddar ham ball or sandwich spread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Shape into a ball and roll in finely chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers or use as spread on crusted bread for party sandwiches.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Mash avocados, then mix with salt, pepper and lemon juice or you can use ready made avocado dip (Kraft).
Mix together sour cream, mayo and taco season mix.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Stir together pretzels, melted butter and 2 tablespoons sugar. Press into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake for 10 minutes. Cool completely.

title: orange-cumin beef tenderloin
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine zest, cumin seed, garlic, thyme, pepper, chili powder, brown sugar and salt.
Brush meat with oil.
Rub spice mixture over meat.
Place in roasting pan. Roast until meat is done, about 45 minutes for medium-rare.
Let stand 15 minutes before slicing.
Makes 12 servings.

title: peanut butter oatmeal candy
directions: Mix oatmeal, margarine, vanilla and peanut butter in large mixing bowl.
In saucepan, bring to boil, sugar, cocoa and milk, stirring constantly to take lumps out.
When melted, pour over oatmeal mixture mixing well.
Place in glass pan.
Better when served cold!

title: squash puppies
directions: Mix ingredients well and cook in deep fat as you would hushpuppies.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Combine all
ingredients
and
add
turkey giblets with broth until mixed
to consistency.
Butter baking pan and bake until golden brown on top at 350°.

title: baked chicken breast with apricot sauce
directions: Melt oleo and oil in shallow pan.
Coat chicken with flour and salt.
Roast for 25 minutes at 375°.
Combine apricot jam, mustard and yogurt.
Spread on chicken.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Brown almonds.
Sprinkle on top.
Serve with rice.
Serves 8.

title: bread and butter pickles(frozen)
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed and mustard seed; pour over cucumbers and onions.
Put in refrigerator for 24 hours, then bag and freeze.

title: busy day stew
directions: Brown meat
in	heavy pan.
Add everything to crock-pot and leave; come
home
to
dinner.
Cook
on medium heat for 4 hours, or until vegetables are tender.
Add your own spices as your family likes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg yolks.
Stir in condensed milk and lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until they form peaks.
Add sugar; beat until stiff.
Spread on top of pie, sealing carefully to the edges.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, or until the meringue is golden brown.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Rinse the chicken pieces and wipe dry.
Heat oil and bacon fat in large skillet.
Brown the chicken pieces and sprinkle with salt, pepper and cayenne pepper. Remove from the pan and set aside.

title: spicy mustard dip
directions: Blend well; serve with any meat dish.

title: dill pickle bites
directions: Lay 2 slices ham side by side, overlapping.
Spread cream cheese at seams.
Lay ham over seam.
Spread cream cheese over all ham.
Place pickle at end of ham and roll ham and pickle up. Chill.
Slice and serve.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Cook 4 slices of bacon.
Saute	onions	in bacon grease until limp, but not brown.
Add
vinegar,
catsup
and
brown sugar. Heat, stirring frequently.	Mix
into
beans and place in large baking dish.
Top with
chopped
raw
bacon.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about an hour.

title: beefaroni
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer, covered, for about 20 minutes or until the macaroni is tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat chicken at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Cut into pieces. Mix together chicken, broccoli, and soups and put in casserole dish.
Mix together mayonnaise and lemon juice; spread over casserole.
Mix together cheese and bread crumbs; spread over top of casserole.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown meat, onion and oil.
Add spices, bread crumbs and water.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: sugarless muffins
directions: Mix thoroughly the flour, milk, mayonnaise and Sweet 'N Low. Stir in berries.
Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Fill about half full and bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 6 to 8 muffins.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Blend lemon juice into condensed milk.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple (it must be well drained) and nuts; spoon into pie shells and refrigerate.

title: coconut cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter or margarine, cream cheese and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating at a medium speed of an electric mixer, until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Before measuring, sift 3 cups of flour and re-sift with baking powder and salt.
Add sifted ingredients to creamed mixture at a low speed, mixing only until well blended.
Fold in the coconut and flavorings.

title: cheesy corn casserole
directions: Place corn in bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Mix eggs and cottage cheese and pour over corn. Mix flour in beef and cook for 1 minute. Add tomato sauce, garlic and cinnamon to meat layer on top. Top with cheese. Bake in 350° oven until heated through.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Put raisins and nuts in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain. Mix all ingredients.
Fill greased or paper lined muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Can bake in tube pan for 1 hour or loaf pan.
Makes 26 muffins.

title: mysterious raspberry jam
directions: Mix the sugar into ground tomatoes in a large kettle. Boil for 15 minutes. Remove from heat and add one large package raspberry gelatin right from the box. Pour into screw top jars and refrigerate. So easy, delicious!
The tomato seeds even make it look like real raspberry jam. I use less tomatoes and sugar.

title: snow ball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 4 Tbsp. hot water; add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple juice; mix in drained pineapple. Set aside in refrigerator until syrupy (about 15 minutes). Whip 2 packages dream whip according to directions, add to gelatin mixture.

title: sweet & sour slaw
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together pour over other ingredients.
Mix well.

title: salad
directions: Toss together and serve.

title: raspberry vinaigrette
directions: Combine and serve on leafy lettuce.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Peel and core apples and set aside.
Boil 10 minutes or until candy melts the remaining ingredients to make syrup; stir often. Cook apples in syrup until tender.
Turn apples in syrup while cooking to color evenly; do not overcook.
Cook just until fork-tender and they are red.
Place apples in dish and pour remaining syrup over them.
Place in refrigerator.
Will keep at least a week.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add flour, sugar, butter, nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns and mix with the rest of the ingredients, except corn flakes and melted oleo.
Combine oleo and crushed corn flakes and sprinkle on top of the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in 3-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and boil 3 minutes. Spoon on semi cooled cake. Let set or can be refrigerated. Enjoy.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place in plastic bag, sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and biscuits, cut into 1/4's.
Shake.
Place in tube pan.
Add nuts if desired. Melt butter, brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan.

title: quick stew 'n dumplings
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Add soup, water and meat; bring to boil.
Meanwhile, combine biscuit mix and milk.
To make 8 dumplings, drop dough from spoon into simmering stew.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat 10 minutes.
Cover; continue cooking 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stew beef casserole
directions: Cut beef into small pieces. Cook in enough water to make 2 cups of broth. Melt margarine; pour into 9 x 13-inch dish. Add soup, broth and rice. Place cooked beef on top. Salt and pepper to taste. Cover and bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: quick fudge
directions: Melt the chocolate drops in the microwave.
Add nuts or peanut butter, if desired.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch buttered plate. Cool; cut into squares.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together cucumbers, onions, red pepper in large bowl. Combine sugar, vinegar and spices until sugar is dissolved.
Pour mixture over cucumber mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, pack into plastic or glass containers and chill for 3-4 days before serving.
Store in refrigerator.
These can be frozen.
Be sure to defrost in refrigerator and leave 1 inch space of top container to allow for expansion.

title: dream pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until knife comes out clean.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning mix.
Put in bottom of casserole dish.
Spread refried beans.
Top with sour cream.
Top with taco sauce (hot or mild).
Top with shredded lettuce.
Top with shredded cheese.
May eat cold or heat in microwave until cheese melts.

title: wheat germ brownies
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs, wheat germ, molasses, nuts, vanilla and salt.
Sift in milk and baking soda.
Stir.
Place in 8-inch square pan, heavily greased. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out of pan and cut while hot.
One cup of raisins or chocolate chips may be added before baking.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice by package directions.
Saute celery and onions in butter and mix with soup and 2/3 jar of Cheez Whiz. Mix other ingredients and put remainder of Cheez Whiz on top. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli-beef squares
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Heat 1 inch salted water to boiling.
Add broccoli. Cover and heat to boiling.
Cook until almost tender, about 5 minutes; drain thoroughly.
Cook and stir beef in 10-inch skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in mushrooms, 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese and the onion.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole; set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan; add cheese.
Blend in milk and sour cream. Add onions and bacon.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: marinade for dove or venison to be cooked over charcoal
directions: Melt butter and add remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly. Marinate doves or venison for several hours before grilling.
Doves should be grilled until slightly pink at the breastbone and venison until degree of doneness you prefer.

title: chicken suzanne
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper; brown in melted margarine.
Remove to greased shallow casserole.
Add sour cream, sherry and mushroom soup to melted margarine.
Mix well and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
If using boneless, skinless chicken breasts, it will finish cooking sooner, so check after 45 minutes.
If your pan is nonstick, you will need only a few tablespoons of margarine, not the whole stick.

title: blueberry banana tea loaf
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture alternating with bananas to creamed mixture.
Mix flour just to blend in.
Stir in blueberries.
Turn into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Loosen sides and turn out on rack.
Cool completely.
(Can be frozen up to 3 months.)

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix first 9 ingredients; place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake for 15 minutes at 450°.

title: pork chops
directions: Dip chops in egg and roll in meal.
Brown and place separately in casserole dish.
Pour onion and mushroom soup over chops. Sprinkle with sharp cheese.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour or until tender.
May be prepared at the last moment and refrigerated until ready to bake.

title: rice krispies caramel bars
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add 1 1/2 bags marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add 8 cups Rice Krispies.
Mix and spread half of mixture on bottom of a greased jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 bag of marshmallows over top.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put pie filling in a dish.
Melt butter and mix in flour and sugar (it will be crumbly).
Pour over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until done.
Very good and easy.

title: mama's butter rolls
directions: *Or substitute refrigerated biscuits.

title: briar patch bake
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce and onions. Heat.
Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed on box except use 1/2 cup milk.
Layer half macaroni and cheese in 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Cover with meat mixture.
Top with remaining macaroni and cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Great with salad and bread.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix remaining ingredients with broccoli.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date chews
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in a greased 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pineapple over pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over pineapple.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 2 tablespoons brown sugar; set aside.
Mix ingredients; pour 1/2 batter into well-greased tube pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cinnamon and sugar mixture, then add remaining batter.
Then sprinkle rest of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake about 50 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix well in a large bowl with a wooden spoon.
Pour into the pie crust and chill before serving.

title: imitation crab casserole
directions: In
large
pot, melt butter or margarine.
Saute onion, celery and mushrooms.
Add imitation crab and seasonings; mix well.
Add eggs
and	mayonnaise; mix well.
Add croutons and peas;
mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish (spray
with Pam
first).
Pan
should remain covered for the first 30 minutes. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: Brown turkey with onion flakes; set aside.
Saute onion, green pepper, mushrooms, onion powder and lawry seasoning all together. Add meat back in.
In big fry pan add the tomatoes, paste and water.
Then simmer all together for 15 minutes.
In a 13x9-inch pan put a little sauce in bottom and add 8 oz. egg noodles, then pour sauce over all.
Sprinkle mozzarella cheese on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover with foil.

title: sesame-soy roast
directions: Brown sesame seed in butter for 1 minute over medium heat in shallow pan.
Add coffee, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and vinegar.
Heat to boiling.
Pour marinade over roast and marinate overnight, covered.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Grease casserole dish.
Top with Cheez-Its crumbs.
Pour 1 stick of melted margarine over crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until it bubbles real well.

title: mandarin orange dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Chill thoroughly.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine sugar, butter and Crisco in mixer. Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, corn syrup and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Mix sugar and cream well.
Microwave for 13 minutes on High. Remove, add pecans, butter and vanilla.
Beat slightly and drop by tablespoons on wax paper.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 250°F oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions. Drain the broccoli and mix with the cooked rice, cheeze wiz, and cream of mushroom soup. Stir all ingredients well. Pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° in the oven for about 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: yams and apricots
directions: In a large saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Add the margarine and sugar, stirring until melted.
Blend in mashed yams with a wooden spoon.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Put in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
(Freeze now, if desired.)
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil.
Combine dry ingredients; add egg mixture. Stir in carrot and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: goat cheese salad
directions: Slice goat cheese to 1/2-inch thick.
Marinate goat cheese in pesto for 2 to 3 hours.
Remove cheese from marinade and dip in bread crumb and thyme mixture.
Bake goat cheese for 4 minutes in a 425° oven; do not overcook.
Toast French bread slices.
Mix watercress or lettuce with Italian dressing.
Arrange on a large platter or individual plates.
Place goat cheese, sun-dried tomatoes and Calamata olives on platter or plates.
Take a slice of French bread; spread with goat cheese.
Add tomato, a little lettuce and onion.

title: tuna mushroom casserole
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, butter and onion in a medium bowl. Mix well.
Place 1/3 of the crumb mixture in a casserole.
Cover with half of the tuna.
Repeat layers, ending with a crumb layer. Pour 1 cup milk on top.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: blackened and stuffed mahi mahi
directions: You will also need a griddle plate or iron skillet.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with half the bread cubes.
Layer 1/2 of the 4 ounce cream cheese cubes on top of bread.
Arrange remaining half of bread cubes and cream cheese cubes.
Blend eggs, maple syrup and milk in blender.
Pour over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: honokaka - swedish style bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour and salt.
Mix sugar and yeast in a cup.
Combine sugar-yeast with melted butter and milk.
Take 2 to 3 cups of mixture and stir into bowl of flour.
Let stand until dough doubles in size.
Knead dough.
Cut dough into chunks and roll to 1/4-inch.
Let rise to 2/4-inch.
Mark dough with fork and bake at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Clean and cut all vegetables into bite size chunks.
Mix together with cooked spaghetti.
Pour dressing over and toss well. Refrigerate overnight, if possible.

title: sweet-sour spareribs with pineapple
directions: Marinate
spareribs
in
ginger
juice, salt, shoyu and cornstarch;
let
stand for 30 minutes.
Heat oil in saucepan; add garlic
and
brown.
Fry
ribs
until
golden brown.
Add liquid, vinegar and sugar; simmer until tender.
Add thickening
made
of 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water. Arrange pineapple on platter.
Pour ribs over it; garnish with Chinese parsley.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Simmer vegetables in 2 cups of water and tomato juice until tender.
Add beef and simmer 5 more minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with corn bread on a cold day.

title: all purpose buttercream frosting
directions: Measure first 5
ingredients into mixing bowl.
Start beater on low speed.
Then 3 minutes on medium speed to form smooth paste.
Add Crisco or cake shortening and continue to mix on medium speed for 5 minutes.

title: potato romano
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in buttered casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Add pumpkin and eggs; mix thoroughly.
Line cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Spread mixture onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Place on towel and roll.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients until creamy to make the filling.
Fill, re-roll and refrigerate.

title: fizzy fruit slush
directions: In a 2-quart pitcher, combine pineapple juice, water, orange juice concentrate, banana and honey; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover and freeze several hours or until firm.
To serve, thaw juice mixture at room temperature about 30 minutes or until able to scrape surface of mixture to form a slush.
For each serving, place 1/3 cup of the slush in a glass and add 1/4 cup of soda.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pecan puff balls
directions: Kream buttah, sugah 'n vanillah...add flour 'n nuts...mix gud 'n chill dough fur at least 30 minutes...Role dough in small balls 'n put on a greasy cookie pan...bake at 350° fur about 12 minutes 'n cool on rack.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together; blend in other ingredients. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: raspberry freeze pie
directions: In large bowl, blend sherbet and yogurt together, mixing well. Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie shell.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Freeze until firm.
Defrost 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first six ingredients and pour into casserole.
Crush one section of Ritz crackers over top and pour one stick of melted butter over crackers.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate scotch bars
directions: Measure syrup and sugar into large pan. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until sugar dissolves and mixture boils. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies to mixture. Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chips over low heat. Spread over cereal mixture. Let stand to set. Cut and eat.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Cook onions and pepper in margarine until tender.
Peel and cut fresh or canned tomatoes and measure 6 cups.
Mix with all ingredients except 1/2 cup bread cubes.
Sprinkle top with remaining bread cubes and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: crab rangoon
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except won ton skins and oil.
Place 1 teaspoon filling in the center of each won ton skin.
Moisten edges with water.
Fold each skin in half to form a triangle.
Press edges to seal.
Pull bottom corners of triangle down and overlap slightly.
Moisten one corner with water and press to seal.
Heat oil to 375°.
Deep fry several won tons at a time, turning once, until both sides are golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce or hot mustard sauce.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, shortening and white sugar.
Add vanilla, eggs and peanut butter.
Sift and add a little at a time the flour.
Roll dough into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press each ball with back of floured fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix beans, taco seasoning and Tabasco sauce together and spread on 9-inch plate.
Layer with rest of ingredients according to how they are listed.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs 3 minutes; gradually add sugar.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes. Turn onto a towel.
Roll up and let cool.

title: hawaiian pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in small bowl.
Chill 15 minutes. Roll into ball and roll into nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: sausage apple stuffing
directions: Mix in very large bowl.
Stuff bird or bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add milk and melted butter. Pour in flavoring and add baking powder.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean.

title: cadillac golden cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake as directed, except decrease water to 3/4 cup and add remaining ingredients to batter before beating. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: flan
directions: Place a pan with water in the oven to heat up (about 1 inch). Make caramel with the sugar.
Pour in the mold and try to cover the sides.
Be careful; is very hot.
Mix the rest of the ingredients well and pour it in the mold.
Put the mold in the pan with water.

title: rivel soup
directions: Rub flour and eggs together until you have crumbles or rivels. Cook this in clear chicken broth until cooked.

title: macaroni and cream of mushroom
directions: Add the macaroni to boiling water.
Cook until done.
Brown ground beef in a covered skillet; drain off excess grease.
Mix ground beef and macaroni.
Add to this the cream of mushroom soup. Do not leave in metal pan or sitting out as mushrooms will become poisonous.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients onto a piece of waxed paper.
In medium bowl, combine onion, corn and beaten eggs.
Blend in melted butter, milk and sifted dry ingredients.
Fry on each side until golden brown.
Serve with ham or fried chicken.

title: basic herb stuffing
directions: Heat corn oil in frypan over medium heat.
Add onion; saute until golden brown.
Add remaining ingredients; toss.
Make about 3 1/2 cups, enough for 2 broiler-fryers.

title: pineapple fluff cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and undrained mandarin oranges in bowl; mix well.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until layers test done.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Spread frosting between layers and over top and side of cake.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: teresa's chicken rolls
directions: Chop cooked chicken.
Add other ingredients.
Tear apart rolls.
Put chicken mixture in widest part of rolls.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes.

title: tuna patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl, form into patties and cook in very little oil until brown on each side.

title: festive cheese ball
directions: Let the 2 cheeses get very soft at room temperature.
When soft enough to blend together, mix in the onion, pepper and pimento.
Chill in fridge until cheese can be handled to form a ball (30 minutes).
When formed, then roll in chopped walnuts, pecans or parsley.
Quarter an olive for the top.
Keep in fridge until used.
Serve with crackers.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix with spoon and pour into graham cracker crust.
Use crushed graham crackers to garnish.
Lemonade should thaw slightly before using.
Let set in refrigerator a while until it is ready to be sliced.

title: bride's chicken(so easy, even a bride can't mess it up!)
directions: Put all ingredients, except peas, in a deep casserole and cover.
Put in a 350° oven 2 1/2 hours.
Don't peek!
When done, add your can of peas.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add spices. Add grated Spam. Continue cooking. Add Mozzarella cheese. After cheese melts through, stir in tomato sauce. After warmed through, spoon onto hamburger buns. Top with small square of Velveeta cheese or Kraft singles. Bake at 350° until toasted and cheese melts.

title: plain pastry (two crust)
directions: Use no water if liquid fat is used.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Beat egg and combine with broccoli and corn.
Place in casserole. Sprinkle stuffing mix on top. Drizzle with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green rice
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix lightly.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for about 1 hour or until set.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: reese marbled pie with rice krispie pie crust
directions: Combine cereal crumbs, sugar and 6 tablespoons butter with a fork.
Using the back of a spoon, press mixture inside a 9-inch pie plate to cover bottom and sides evenly.
Bake at 375 for 5-6 minutes; set on wire rack to cool.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir 2 minutes, then remove from heat. Stir a moderate amount of the hot mixture into yolks and immediately return to hot mixture in pan.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly, and remove from heat.
Add butter and peanut butter and let mixture cool to lukewarm.
Barely stir in chocolate chips, so mixture looks marbled.
Pour into crust. Prepare meringue by beating egg whites, vanilla and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff and glossy peaks form and all sugar is dissolved.
Spread meringue over warm filling, sealing to edge of pie shell.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Sift together.
Put in sauce, cook over flame stirring constantly until boiling, boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1/4 cup peanut butter and 1 1/2 cups oats, stir to combine. Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet, let cool.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add buttermilk to sugar and butter. Beat eggs lightly and add to mixture, stirring lightly.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Cook 10 minutes at 375°.
Lower heat to 300° and bake 40 minutes more until done. (From "A Taste of Georgia.")

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Sift 3 times flour, cocoa and salt.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with buttermilk, then add vanilla and food coloring.
Beat well.
Fold in soda dissolved with vinegar.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool on cake racks.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package.
Drain well.
Combine cottage cheese, yogurt, egg and salt.
Add shredded cheese.
Mix well; stir in cooked macaroni.
Spread in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix milk, sugar and butter.
Scald and cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add this to milk mixture.
Add 8 cups flour.
Cover and let rise until double in size. Stir down and add 1 cup flour to other ingredients.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Shape as many rolls as you want.
Let rise and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until brown. Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in casserole dish.
Layer corn and cooked macaroni over ground beef.
Pour tomato sauce over macaroni and bake at 350° until bubbly and heated through.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add milk, vanilla and enough boiling water to mix well.
Cook until of pudding consistency.

title: cream cheese treats
directions: Get slices of bread and take off the crusts.
Flatten the bread and cut it in 1 1/2-inch rows.
On one side of the bread, spread cream cheese.
On the opposite side, spread butter.
Put cinnamon on the buttered side.
Roll it up with the cinnamon side out.
Eat and enjoy.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water.
Cool.
Mix lime Kool-Aid and pineapple juice into sweetened water.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add celery and onions; cook until celery is tender.
Use no seasoning.
Add soups and noodles; mix together. Place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Makes large hot dish.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to other mixture.
Stir in nuts and apples. Pour into greased tube pan with paper lined bottom.
Put into cold oven.
Set oven to 350°.
Cook for 70 minutes or until done. Remove from pan while hot.
Glaze with following.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Whisk in bowl the egg whites, water and syrup.
Mix dry ingredients together; then add to egg white mixture.
Pour into Pam-sprayed 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes before eating.
Keeps well and tastes even better the next day!

title: grilled salmon with raspberry sauce
directions: Split salmon lengthwise down backbone and fillet out.
Remove backbone and place on heavy-duty foil.
Melt butter and stir in remaining ingredients.
Grill salmon on barbecue, basting with sauce until done.
Serves 6.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples, oil and eggs together.
Add sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and vanilla.
Combine flour and pecans.
Add to preceding mixture.
Pour into greased tube pan; bake 45 minutes in 325° oven.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Scald milk with butter.
Soak bread in milk for 10 minutes. Add sugar, salt, slightly beaten egg and vanilla.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, shortening, vanilla, lemon flavoring and milk.
Add dry ingredients, a little at a time. Drop by teaspoon and flatten with a small glass dipped in sugar. Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: peachy fruit kabobs
directions: Cut apples and peaches into 1 1/2-inch wedges.
Soak fruit in water and lemon juice mixture for 5 minutes.
Thread fruit onto skewers, alternating apples, peaches and cherries.
Combine honey and cinnamon in saucepan; cook over medium flame until mixture boils.
Turn off flame.
Preheat gas grill.
Grill on medium setting for 8 to 10 minutes.
Baste with marinade; turn frequently.
Makes 14 servings.

title: berry kissel(russia)
directions: Combine water, berries, and sugar in a saucepan.
Simmer until the berries pop or softened.
Puree the berries in a food mill or processor.
If you want to remove the seeds, strain the puree through with a sieve.
Return the puree to the saucepan.
Mix the cornstarch and orange juice, add to the puree.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently for about 5 minutes until thickened.
Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: rockfish stuffed with skipjack oyster dressing
directions: Wash and dry fish thoroughly.
Sprinkle inside cavity with salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Put in shallow, foil-lined baking pan.
Stuff cavity of fish loosely with dressing and secure edges. Baste liberally with fat or oil.
Bake at 350°, basting frequently, until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork; 40 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed cornish hens burgundy
directions: Cook rice according to package directions and stuff hens. Lightly salt and pepper hens.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Bring the white syrup and brown sugar to a boil.
Add the peanut butter and stir.
Pour this mixture over the Cheerios and Rice Krispies.
Pat into a buttered cookie sheet or cake pan. Melt the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips and spread on the top of the bars.

title: crisp crust dessert squares
directions: Combine cereal, sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Reserve half of this mixture.
Press remaining cereal mixture into bottom of an 8-inch pan.
Prepare pudding mix as directed on box.
Then pour pudding mix over the mixture in the pan.
Use the reserved cereal mixture for topping.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: apple crisp coffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg slightly with fork.
Stir in milk and vegetable oil.
Measure and combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to liquid mixture all at once. Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Add apples to mixture; stir until well blended.
Spread batter into a greased 9 x 1 1/2-inch round layer pan.
Sprinkle with Streusel Topping. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Pull off bone.
Saute onions in margarine.
Combine all other ingredients and add to chicken and onions in oblong dish.
Add enough broth (where chicken was cooked) to make mixture about like thick gravy.
Put crushed cornflakes, potato chips or Stove Top dressing on top and bake at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour (until bubbly).
Mixture will thicken when it cools.

title: sticky rolls
directions: Butter Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts in pan.
Place rolls. Sprinkle pudding over rolls and pour cinnamon, brown sugar and margarine over rolls.
Let rise 4 to 5 hours.

title: mexican egg squares
directions: Trim crusts from bread and spread one side of each with butter.
In 8-inch square baking dish arrange bread, buttered side down, in one layer.
Layer cheeses, chiles and green onion evenly on top.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs with 1 tablespoon sugar and melted margarine. Press onto bottom of 8-inch or 9-inch spring-form pan; chill. Beat cream cheese and 3/4 cup sugar until well blended.
Beat in pumpkin, spices and salt.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Lightly flour chicken.
Heat butter with chopped garlic and saute chicken until cooked through.
Remove chicken and pour off excess butter.
Deglaze pan with lemon juice and Marsala wine.
Put in mushrooms and cook 2 minutes.
Add chicken and gravy and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving portions.
Use chicken fryer; fit ribs in fryer and cover.
Place on medium heat until cover is hot to touch.
Reduce heat to low and cook 30 minutes.
Pour off excess fat and season with salt and pepper.
Turn ribs over and pour sauce over them.
Cover and continue to cook on low for 1 hour.

title: zinger toffee crunch
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.

In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, heat butter, sugar and water over medium temperature, stirring with a wooden spoon, until sugar dissolves. Cover pan with lid for 2 minutes to wash down any sugar crystals. Uncover pan; increase heat to high.
Without stirring, continue cooking until golden brown.
Remove from heat; stir in liqueur and baking soda.
Pour immediately into baking dish; spread thin with wooden spoon and let cool.

title: golden cream soup
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Combine next 3 ingredients.
Combine 2 batches.
Heat over low heat until hot.
Do not boil after adding milk and cheese. Garnish and serve.

title: tuna spread
directions: Mix cream cheese with mustard, folding with olives, dill, garlic and parsley.
Mix well.
Add tuna.
Mix and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: tiny meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls and place 8-inch circle on 7-inch paper plate.
Cover meat balls with plastic wrap.
Cook in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
If frozen, cooking time will be 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Remove plastic wrap and serve with toothpicks.
Makes 40 small meat balls.

title: breakfast moon slush
directions: Blend milk, fruit, wheat germ and ice together.
Serve.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: fruit and nut roll
directions: Mix crushed wafers with milk, add fruits and nuts which have been cut or chopped into fine pieces.
Mix well and form into a roll about 3 inches in diameter. Wrap in wax paper and store in refrigerator until ready to serve, then slice desired thickness.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with skin on in a large pot covered with cold water, do not over cook potatoes. Rinse and drain potatoes, place in refrigerator to cool. Boil eggs. Cool eggs. Cook bacon till crispy. Cook beef bouillon cubes in one cup of water. Cool. Combine in a large bowl the following: Diced celery, bell pepper, red onion, and boiled eggs. Peel red potatoes in cold water, and slice. Hand crumble the crispy bacon. Add the parsley flakes, dill weed salt, pepper, sweet basil, beef bouillon broth, white vinegar, oil and mayonnaise. Gently mix. Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken of oodles
directions: Fry chicken flavor oodles of noodles as directed.
Heat can of cream of chicken soup.
Mix together.
Serves about 4.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Grease a 12 cup muffin pan. Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a medium bowl; make a well in the center.

title: karo pie
directions: Beat butter, flour, sugar, eggs and syrup.
Line unbaked pie shell with pecans.
Pour sugar mixture over pecans.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: sauteed green tomatoes
directions: Combine flour, salt, paprika and nutmeg; mix well.
Cut tomatoes in 1/2-inch slices.
Dip into flour mixture.
Saute slices gently in melted butter.
Place on toast rounds.
Blend the butter and flour left in the skillet with the milk and parsley. When the sauce is smooth and hot, pour it over the tomatoes.

title: bloody mary punch
directions: Combine juice, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce in a pitcher (2-quart). Add ice and sparkling water to fill. Garnish with celery stalks and lemon slices.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Separate crescent rolls and press into 12-inch pizza pan.
Put sausage on top of rolls, then the thawed hash browns, followed by the Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together, then pour over sausage, potatoes and cheese; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting.
Serves about 6.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Grease 9 x 9-inch pan.
Split breasts and put in pan.
Top with spoonfuls of soup, undiluted.
Put slice of cheese on each breast; sprinkle stuffing over cheese.
Melt butter and pour over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (uncovered).

title: easy lemon muffins
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients and pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces.
Combine flour, salt & pepper. Coat meat with seasoned flour. In large frying pan, brown meat in hot oil.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer, covered for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours until tender. Serve with potatoes or noodles.
6 Servings.

title: low carb sherbet
directions: Dissolve jell-o in 1 c. boiling water, let cool. Whip cream. Pour cooled jell-o into whipped cream and gently fold. Set in freezer 20 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetables
directions: Mix all vegetables, ham and cheese together.
Cover with Ranch dressing.
Put in refrigerator.
Will keep for several days.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Pat the chicken pieces dry and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Cover the pieces with the apricot marmalade, then sprinkle on the soup mix and cover with the Russian salad dressing.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Thoroughly beat the margarine, eggs, sugar and cocoa.
Mix flour, baking powder and milk into soft mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: pineapple angel food cake
directions: Beat above ingredients together. Pour into ungreased tube pan. Bake 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven. Cool, turned upside down.

title: oven-fried garlic potatoes
directions: Dip potatoes in oil.
Sprinkle lightly with salt, pepper, garlic salt and parsley.
Place in foil-lined pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until browned.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: summer fresh fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Add and blend Marshmallow Fluff and cherry juice.
Use as dip for fresh fruit.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Heat Eagle Brand milk and chocolate squares in top of double boiler until thick; stir often (about 10 minutes).
Remove from heat; stir in hot water slowly.
Then add cream, vanilla and milk. Put in container (she used pan) in freezer.
When about 2/3 frozen, dump into large mixer bowl and beat until frothy.
Put back in container in freezer.
It will have an icy texture.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil carrots in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Chop onion and pepper.
Mix sugar, mustard and soup.
Add vinegar and oil; mix well.
Pour over cooled carrots, onion and pepper.
Mix lightly and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for 3 hours.
Roll and cut out with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked meat loaf
directions: Combine celery, water, green pepper, onion and broth mix. Cook until celery is tender.
Add to hamburger mixed with other ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: In a saucepan on medium heat, slowly add water to cornstarch. Whisk together over heat.
Stir until it starts to boil around edges.
Add Jell-O and 5 packets Equal.
Mix well.
Mix together cream cheese, 3 packets Equal and milk.
Spread over bottom and sides of pie crust.
Add 6 packets of Equal to strawberries. Blend Jell-O mixture with strawberries.
Pour into crust.
Chill at least 3 hours or overnight.
Top with whipped topping.

title: apple delight
directions: Beat well 3 eggs; add sugar.
Add oil and blend.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Fold in the apples and nuts. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve warm.

title: special brownies
directions: Blend flour and cocoa.
Cream margarine and sugar, then add flour mixture with eggs and vanilla.
Pour mixture into buttered brownie pan (8 x 8-inch, 9 x 9-inch, etc.).
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; carefully position mini marshmallows over entire cake.
If they slide off, moisten slightly and put back.
Return cake to oven for 1 minute; remove immediately.
(The heat "sets" the marshmallows.)
While still warm, top with any chocolate glaze.

title: christmas cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add sugar and set overnight.
Beat whipping cream.
Add marshmallows which have been sliced.
Set overnight.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In large bowl, put cereal and milk and let stand.
Then add banana, cinnamon, egg, vanilla and sugar.
Stir well or beat with mixer.
In another bowl, put flour, bran, salt and baking powder and mix well, then cut in margarine (I use Promise no fat and applesauce) with pastry blender.
Add flour mixture to cereal mixture.
Batter may be stiff, then add blueberries.
Makes 12 muffins (cupcake pan).
Pan can be greased or sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or so.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients except mushrooms.
Bring to a boil.
Add mushrooms.
Simmer 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Chill in covered container overnight.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Bring milk and butter to boil.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt thoroughly and add to sugar and egg mixture.
Add hot milk last. Pour into a greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: grilled basil shrimp
directions: Whisk marinade ingredients in a large bowl until blended.
Add shrimp and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate at least 30 minutes, not more than 2 hours.
Drain shrimp; reserve marinade for basting.
Grill 4 to 6 inches above coals 2 to 3 minutes per side, basting once, until shrimp are pink and barely opaque in center.

title: tangy meatballs
directions: Make meat into balls and bake at 350 degrees. Wash and drain the meatballs, set aside.

title: too good to be true cake
directions: Bake cake according to box in an 11 x 14-inch cake pan.
When done, poke holes in top of cake with wooden spoon handle.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and butterscotch; heat in microwave oven until thin.
Pour over cake; sprinkle Heath Brickle Bits and pecans over cake; let cool.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce and place in bottom of oblong casserole dish. Place each remaining food, layered in order: bell pepper, celery, onion, peas, mayonnaise and cheese.
Top with bacon.
Chill.

title: marinated carrots(copper pennies)
directions: Peel carrots; slice and cook in a small amount of water until tender-crisp.
Drain and cool.
Combine with green pepper and onion.
Combine soup, oil, sugar, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables and marinate in the refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Keeps several days.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix
ingredients all together.
Cook about 30 minutes or until it shakes a little in the middle. Do not overcook.
Serve warm.

title: banana jam bread
directions: Cream the shortening. Add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine bananas and lemon juice. Stir into creamed mixture. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture. Stir in jam and pecans. Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake for 50 minutes. Cool in pans 10 minutes before removing.

title: crunchy double chip cookies
directions: Stir together flour, salt, baking powder and soda; set aside. In large mixing bowl, beat together sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients, mixing until thoroughly combined.
Add 2 cups of the crushed corn flakes and the chocolate and peanut butter morsels. Drop by slightly rounded measuring tablespoonfuls into remaining crushed corn flakes, coating dough completely.
Place 2 inches apart on slightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 12 minutes, or until light golden brown.
Cool; store in airtight container.

title: orange muffins
directions: Grind together peel of 1 orange and 1 cup raisins.
Cream together the sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add buttermilk; beat. Sift together the soda, 1 cup flour and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in the ground orange peel and raisins.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with juice of 2 oranges; put 1 teaspoon over each muffin while still warm.

title: mustard fried chicken
directions: Wipe chicken breasts with damp towel, then sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In
a
bowl beat together egg and mustard. In another bowl,
combine
cheese
and
bread crumbs, mixing well. Dip each chicken
breast
in
egg
mixture until evenly coated. Lay chicken on wax
paper;
let
coating to set for 10 minutes. Saute chicken on both
sides in heated oil for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle with green pepper slices.

title: baked corn
directions: Blend all ingredients and bake slowly at 325° for one hour.

title: breakfast delight
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients for 45 minutes after reaching a boil.
Add cherries, pecans and sugar.
Cook for 15 minutes and put into jars.

title: beef and vegetable casserole
directions: Combine beef, onion, salt, pepper, garlic powder and oregano in a large skillet.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until beef is no longer pink and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Add tomatoes, corn, peas and soup.
Mix well.
Bring to boiling. Cover and lower the heat.
