Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: scalloped potatoes with pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in hot oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Core and chop unpeeled apples.
In medium bowl, combine first 4 ingredients. Add apples, celery and raisins and toss to coat well. Cover and chill until serving time.
Just prior to serving, spoon onto lettuce lined platter.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
(All seasonings are Watkins products.)

title: smoked sausage, bacon 'n beans
directions: Place bacon between paper toweling on paper plate.
Cook on High for 3 minutes; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with plastic wrap and cook on Medium-high for 12 minutes or until heated through, giving dish half a turn once.
Stir, scraping edges.
Lay bacon on top.
Cover and cook on Medium-high for 2 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: szechuan shrimp
directions: Heat oil in a wok or large, heavy skillet.
Add shrimp, green onion, ginger and garlic.
Stir-fry until shrimp are pink.
Add sherry, soy sauce, salt and sugar.
Stir well and blend in catsup, chilli sauce and red pepper flakes.
Serve with hot cooked rice. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all together and place in casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup grated cheese and 1 stack Ritz, crushed.
Bake at 325! until bubbly.

title: low-fat chicken enchiladas
directions: Make a cheese sauce by whisking together 1 cup Pet milk and 1 cup chicken broth and 2 tablespoons flour.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add 3 slices fat-free cheese (stir in on direction when melting fat-free cheese).
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, put small amount of sauce.
Layer 1/2 tortillas, 1/2 chicken, onion and chilies.
Top with 1/2 remaining sauce. Repeat.
Top with Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed, baking in a well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool 15 minutes. Poke with a fork at 1/2-inch intervals. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add cold water and spoon over cake in pan. Chill 3 to 4 hours. Top with Cool Whip.

title: iron skillet apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place butter in large iron skillet. Place in oven and let melt. Then stir in brown sugar and let melt. Place 1st pie crust on top of mixture in skillet. Place sliced apples on top of crust and sprinkle with white granulated sugar and cinnamon mixture. Place second pie crust on top of apple mixture and make small slits in crust. Bake 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: molasses muffins
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Blend in molasses.
Combine soda and buttermilk; add to mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Pour 2/3 full into muffin tins. Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix potatoes and onion together and cook.
Cut potatoes into small chunks.
Add all other ingredients.
Serve hot.

title: pudding squares
directions: In casserole dish or oblong dish, place bread crumbs and melted butter and press along bottom.
Mix pudding (dry), sour cream and milk in bowl.
Pour mixture over pressed crumbs and smooth mixture out.
Pour pie filling over pudding mixture and smooth out on top.
Chill for 2 hours and cut into squares.
Makes 15 to 20 squares.

title: skillet corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels.
Break into large pieces; discard all but 2 tablespoons of bacon grease from skillet.
Add onion and simmer until brown.
Stir in corn, pepper, salt and milk and heat through.
Sprinkle bacon and parsley on top and serve.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix together eggs and sugar. Add the next 6 ingredients and mix together. Pour into a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let cool.

title: refrigerator dills
directions: Put dill in bottom of a 1-gallon jar.
Stuff jar with pickles. Makes 1 gallon plus 2 quarts.
Will keep for weeks in refrigerator.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine and bake like any other cookies.
Milk must be sour to bring out the taste.
To sour milk, add 1 tablespoon lemon juice or vinegar in cup first.
Bake at 350°.

title: potatoes
directions: In large pot, add enough water to cover potatoes; boil until tender.
Cool and peel potatoes.
Mix milk and cheese in pan until melted.
In casserole dish, slice potatoes and add all ingredients.
Bake at 375° until brown, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Whip the cream cheese. Add powdered sugar and mix until well blended.
Add vanilla and blend in salad dressing or mayonnaise. Fold in fruit and marshmallows. Whip the cream and fold into fruit mixture. Add food coloring and mix.
Salad should be pale pink. Ladle into 5-ounce serving or souffle cups.
Freeze immediately, at least overnight.
Defrost about 15 minutes before serving. This is really good.

title: beef-cheese loaves
directions: Saute onion in butter or margarine until soft.
Combine beef, 1 3/4 cups cheese, relish, catsup, salt, Worcestershire and sauteed onion.
Mix gently, but thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 4 to 6 individual loaves.
Turn loaves onto greased baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
About 5 minutes before end of baking time, sprinkle tops of loaves with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate immediately. Serves 8 to 10.

title: dee's best brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In medium microwave-safe bowl, place butter.
Microwave on High 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each, with wooden spoon. Add cocoa.
Beat until well blended.

title: basil cauliflower and sweet pepper
directions: In large saucepan with lid, bring about 1 inch of water to boil.
Place cauliflower in.
Place pepper on top.
Steam for 10 to 15 minutes, until tender or crisp.
Drain; sprinkle with basil. Toss lightly until mixed.

title: fruit dip
directions: Using mixer, blend together Marshmallow Creme and cream cheese.
Fold in sour cream.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve with cut-up fruit.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: You will also need 1 package of skewers.
Peel shrimp and soak in garlic and butter mixture 1 hour.
Put shrimp on skewer and grill until shrimp are pink.

title: fudge stripped cookie dessert
directions: Mix pudding and buttermilk together.
Add whipped topping and fruit.
Crumble 3/4 of cookies and stir into mixture.
Crumble rest of cookies and put on top.

title: mom's apple raisin nut bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil, flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda, vanilla, salt and baking powder in large bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in nuts, raisins and apples until a rather stiff batter is formed.
Mix until all ingredients are thoroughly blended, but don't overmix.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until center comes out clean.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix together with pastry blender; refrigerate overnight or several hours.
Break off small pieces of dough and press into tart pans.

title: kids' krunch
directions: Melt butter with sugar and corn syrup.
Pour over cereal. Toss.
Put on cookie sheet and put in 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes. Pour on waxed paper to cool.

title: banana split smoothie
directions: Combine bananas, pineapple, ice, orange juice and sugar in container of an electric blender.
Top with cover; process until smooth.
Add yogurt and process until blended.
Serve immediately.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, cheese, onion,
mayonnaise, salt, pepper and sugar; put in casserole.
Mix butter and cracker crumbs; sprinkle on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until topping is brown.

title: coconut pecan caramel pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add coconut and pecans; brown lightly.
Set aside to cool.
Combine the softened cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk, using a mixer.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Put 1/4 of this mixture into each pie shell.
Drizzle 1/4 jar of the caramel topping on each, then sprinkle with 1/4 of the coconut mixture on each pie.
Repeat layers on each pie.
Freezes well.
Serve right from the freezer.

title: pastry mix
directions: Mix salt and flour.
Cut lard into the flour with a pastry blender until the pieces are the size of small peas.
Store in a tightly covered container in the refrigerator until ready for use. Two cups of mix will be sufficient for a large two-crust pie.

title: country chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Blend ingredients lightly and put in a 9 x 13 casserole.

title: italian biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg and flavoring.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto greased baking pan.
Bake until light brown, about 10 minutes. Cool.
Finish with a light white frosting and sprinkle with candy sprinkles.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Note:
Also good plain, omitting nuts and raisins.

title: potato-spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese. Pour into Pam-sprayed 2-quart casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes. Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes longer. Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Generously
grease
large
cookie sheet with butter and set aside.
Combine
sugar and corn syrup in 2 to 2 1/2-quart glass bowl.
Microwave
on
High
4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts with wooden spoon; cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla. Cook on High 2 minutes.
Add baking soda; stir until light
and foamy.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet and spread quickly,
using back
of
wooden spoon.
Let cool, then break into pieces.
Store in airtight container in cool place.

title: apple crunch
directions: Remove apple cores.
Slice apples thin and place into an ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon over the apples.
Combine the margarine, sugar and flour in a bowl and mix well. Pour the mixture over the apples by hand.
Bake for 30 minutes or until apples are soft at 375°.
Serve hot or cold. Spoon cake out and serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: nasty cake(good n' gooey)
directions: This is a very easy chocolate cake and is very moist.

title: lickity quick lemonade bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except the 1/3 cup lemonade concentrate in large mixing bowl.
Blend well.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Pour batter into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Loosen bread from edges of pan.
Pour the reserved 1/3 cup of concentrate over bread.
Cool; remove from pan.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
In a bowl beat real good, eggs, sugar, vanilla and Ricotta cheese.
Spread over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Enjoy.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop up both artichokes and chilies in processor.
Put on bottom of greased casserole dish.
Carefully spread mayonnaise on top.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly or microwave on High until hot and bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes and margarine in a large Ziploc bag.
Melt margarine in a baking dish.
Rinse potatoes and place in flour mixture inside bag.
Coat well and place potatoes in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes on each side.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Let sugar and milk boil for a few minutes.
Add dates.
Stir and mash dates while cooking.
Cook to the soft ball stage; add oleo, nuts and vanilla.
Knead with spoon well.
Roll in damp cloth and allow to harden.
Unroll and cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: camp grier vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine ingredients in mixer.
In a 4-quart churn, add whole milk to mixture to bring level to fill line.
Churn until hard.

title: blender gazpacho
directions: Blend all, chill and serve with croutons.

title: butter icing
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Stir in cream and vanilla.
Add egg yolk.

title: sour cream tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with sour cream, mixing well after each addition.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Knead with flour on lightly floured surface and work dough with enough flour until easy to handle.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with 3-inch round cookie cutter. Place on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening and cool. Add 1 cup sugar, molasses, and egg; mix well. Combine flour, baking soda, salt, and spices; add to sugar mixture. Mix until blended. Shape into 1 inch balls; roll in sugar. Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets and bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until done. Yield: about 4 dozen cookies.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice.
Add sugar and stir.
Add beaten eggs, milk and vanilla.
Cook on low heat and stir until mixture thickens.
Do not boil.
Add raisins.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.

title: all in one meal
directions: In a large frying pan, brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add corn, tomatoes, water and macaroni.
Stir until all mixed, cutting up tomatoes as you stir.
Heat until boiling, then turn heat down to low.
Stir occasionally.
Cook until macaroni is done.
Add cheese package and stir.
Serves 6.

title: chinese fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
(I find that a Teflon pan works better.)
Combine all ingredients.
Pack into pan.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes.
If you prefer, you can use loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: chicken divan
directions: Put chicken breasts in baking dish.
Blend softened cream cheese, Italian dressing and cooking sherry.
Pour on top of chicken.
Pour melted butter over top of all.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches in 9 x 13-inch pan; cover over with cake mix. Melt oleo and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon of milk and 1 tablespoon of sugar with wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk with 2 packages of pudding and beat with wire whip until blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and spices.
Mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Garnish with additional Cool Whip and nuts.

title: curried "4" fruit bake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter; add sugar and curry powder. Drain and dry fruit.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add butter mixture.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered.
Serve with ham, pork or chicken.

title: russel stover's candy
directions: Melt margarine; mix in milk, coconut and chopped pecans.
Add box of powdered sugar.
Mix up together.
Chill for 2 hours; roll into balls.
Coat balls in melted chocolate.

title: delicious chicken dumplings
directions: Bring soup and water or milk to boil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add chunks of chicken from can.
Peel flaky biscuits apart and drop layers into boiling mixture, being sure to continue stirring frequently.
When all biscuits have been added, cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, watching closely to prevent sticking.

title: white house pecan pie
directions: Allow butter to stand in medium mixing bowl until very soft. Add sugar, syrup, salt and vanilla.
Beat until thoroughly blended. Add eggs and beat gently just until blended.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for about 40 to 45 minutes or until top is toasted brown and filling is set in center.
Makes 1 pie.

title: bonbon nuts
directions: Have cream cheese and butter at room temperature and cream together.
Add flour and mix as for pie crust.
Chill 1 hour. Roll out with powdered sugar (work with 1/3 of dough at a time). Cut into strips.
Wrap strips around pecan halves.
Bake at 375° about 15 to 17 minutes.
Yields 9 dozen.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Stir jello with water until dissolved.
Add strawberries, pineapple, banana and nuts.
Mix together sour cream, sugar and lemon juice.
Add marshmallows.
Spread on top of firm jello.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat yogurt with brown sugar (or substitute), vinegar, salt and mustard and hot broccoli.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: thick creme fraiche
directions: Combine creams in mixing bowl and whisk lightly together. Cover bowl loosely with plastic and leave at room temperature overnight for the culture to develop. At the end of maturing time, the cream mixture will be tart and thick.
Transfer to bowl and chill for 4 hours or longer in refrigerator.
Creme Fraiche will keep for 2 or 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: jambalaya stir-fry
directions: Heat butter with the oil in large heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic, onions, bell peppers, and celery. Cook until peppers and celery are almost tender.

Stir in ham. Add shrimp and cook, stirring constantly, 3 minutes or until shrimp change color from gray to pink. Combine lemon juice, soy sauce, and cornstarch. Mix well and stir into shrimp/pepper mixture.
Add chili powder and mix well.
Continue cooking until mixture is slightly thickened.
Serve over rice.
Sprinkle with almonds.

title: better than anything
directions: Mix together and put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool!

title: baked salmon
directions: Grease casserole with butter.
Roll salmon in bread crumbs. Lay in casserole and top with lemon juice and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: champagne peaches(serves 6)
directions: Dip 12 peaches into boiling water for 1/2 minute; remove and rinse in cold water.
Peel peaches and cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Sweeten peaches with 1/2 cup sugar in bowl; mix well by hand.
Chill.
Put peaches in table size serving dish.
Pour champagne over peaches.
Let chill until time to serve.

title: mmmpossible cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate.
Place milk, vanilla, eggs, sugar and Bisquick in blender container.
Cover and blend on high for 15 seconds.
Add cream cheese.
Cover and blend on high for 2 minutes.
Pour into plate.
Bake until center is firm, 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: cinnamon cut-outs
directions: Combine both ingredients; mix well.
Shape into interesting shapes or roll out and use cookie cutters.
If using cookie cutters, roll out to 1/4-inch.
This must dry for several days. Use throughout your home for aroma.

title: chilly-day chili
directions: Cook and stir ground beef in a large skillet until meat is slightly browned.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Season with salt, pepper, onion powder and chili powder according to your own taste.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Steam broccoli or prepare in microwave.
Let cool.
Cut in 1-inch pieces and mix with other ingredients.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.
This will keep 3 to 4 days.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; beat.
Add flour, salt and soda; beat.
Add oats; beat.
Blend in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: chicken and chip casserole
directions: Mix rice, chicken soup, and milk;
set aside.
Melt butter in sauce pan, add celery and onions, cook over low heat until onion is transparent; remove from heat, and stir in frozen mushrooms and chicken.
Add this to rice and chicken soup and mix well.
Put 1 1/2 c. of potato chips into buttered casserole.
Carefully pour in the chicken, rice, and vegetable mixture.
Top with the remainder of potato chips.
Bake in 325° oven for 35 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: just for kids: rusty's roly-poly's
directions: Sift flour.
Add cream of tartar, soda and salt.
In separate bowl, cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture and blend well.
Chill dough in refrigerator for 2 hours or until easy to handle.

title: hamburger dressing
directions: Fry hamburger, salt, pepper, onion and celery until brown. Add potatoes, bread, soup and milk.
Put in casserole; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: In a large bowl add all the ingredients and mix well.
Add 1 can Baker's Angel Flake coconut.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream
butter
and
shortening well.
Add sugar slowly, then add sour
cream.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Beat in eggs and flavorings.
Mix
flour,
soda
and
salt;	add to batter. Beat for
minutes.
Grease and lightly flour a 10-inch tube pan. Pour in
and
bake	for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325° or until cake tests done.

title: tuna crunch casserole
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup of noodles.
Combine remaining ingredients. Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with reserved noodles. Bake at 325° uncovered in preheated slow oven for 40 minutes.

title: pecan pies
directions: Place pecan halves real close together in pie crusts. Pour the mixture, which has been heated enough to melt the butter, over the nuts. (Beat egg whites and yolks together for best results.) Place in oven and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until top is golden brown and filling is thick. Serve with whipped cream if desired. Yields 2 pies.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Blend and melt the first 3 ingredients in top of double boiler.
Cool.
Whip the cream and mix with cooled mixture.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Set in refrigerator.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat the sugar and cocoa in saucepan for 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add the margarine and evaporated milk.
Boil until it starts to get fairly thick.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla.

title: fruit cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Chop fruit and break nuts.
Mix dry ingredients and mix with fruit.
Beat eggs. Add vanilla and pour over fruit. Bake 1 hour in greased pans lined with wax paper at 300°.

title: chicken or pork adobo
directions: Season chicken or pork with salt and pepper.
Place in saucepan and add ginger, garlic and vinegar.
Let simmer for 1 hour on low heat or until tender.
If water is needed, add 1/4 cup water.
Add more salt or shoyu to taste, if necessary.
When meat is tender, saute with vegetable oil until browned.
Serve hot.

title: delicious coconut pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix and 2 1/2 cups milk in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add coconut extract and 1 cup coconut flakes.
Pour mixture into a bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and let cool completely.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Scald
milk;
when lukewarm, add sugar, salt and yeast. Let stand
minutes.
Add
1/2 cups of flour; beat well. Cover and let rise until light.
Add well beaten eggs, melted shortening and
remainder of flour; mix thoroughly.
Let rise again
until doubled in bulk.
Roll out approximately 1/2 inch thick.
Brush with melted butter; sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon,
raisins
and nuts.
Roll
like
a jelly roll and cut in 1-inch slices; let rise.
Bake about 15 minutes at 400°.

title: lime slush
directions: Place pitted nectarines with skin on in blender, cut them in pieces first.
Add 1 can frozen limeade.
Add 1 tray ice cubes. Blend until it's slush.
Good in the summer.

title: pepperoni roll ups
directions: Unroll crescent rolls in one piece (forms rectangle).
Pinch at dotted seams.
Top with pepperoni and cheese.
Fold dough to form roll.
Bake according to package.
Slice and serve.

title: candied keebler crackers
directions: Coat cookie sheet (with sides) with Pam or any spray coating. Place crackers on cookie sheet 1/4 inch apart.
Cook butter and sugar 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Spoon over crackers, covering well.
Sprinkle crushed nuts on each cracker.
Be generous.
Bake in 325° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Watch close. Should be light brown.
Yummy!

title: lemon bread
directions: Beat oleo, sugar and eggs together; then add dry ingredients, alternately with milk and extracts.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cheryl's hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add corn, tomatoes, Worcestershire, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: lorraine's mock sour cream pie
directions: Cook the raisins in the water until tender and dry.
Add the milk, sugar, flour and salt.
Cook until thick.
Add the nutmeg and egg yolks.
Remove from the stove; add the vinegar.
Top with meringue.
Makes 2 small pies.

title: orange drink
directions: Mix orange kool aid as package directs.
Add 1/2 cup Tang and orange slices.

title: no-cook lemon freeze
directions: Combine crumbs, first sugar and butter in 8-inch pie pan or ice cube tray.
Mix well; save 2 to 4 tablespoons for topping.

title: beet relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl and blend well; chill thoroughly.

title: cheese-potato puffs
directions: Cook peeled potatoes in salted water until tender.
Drain; mash thoroughly.
Add butter, cheese, milk and salt; heat over low heat until butter and cheese is melted.
Fold in eggs and pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
May make ahead.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until puffy
and golden brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix well.
Put in an airtight bowl.
Put in refrigerator for at least 8 hours.
Roll out in small ball in palm of hand.
Press on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.
Must bake within 3 days.

title: tuna spread
directions: Boil the potatoes in the skins until tender; peel, then mash. Add milk; beat until smooth.
Add tuna, salt and pepper; mix well. Mold in a fish shape or in any form you particularly like.
Serve very cold with a dressing of the mayonnaise.
Serves 4.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and jello in saucepan until blended.
Add boiling water and oleo.
Cook until it thickens slightly.
Cool and add sliced strawberries.
Pour in a baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream, Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: buttermilk doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add oil and vanilla.
Add flour, etc., with the buttermilk.
When well mixed, put on floured board and roll out about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry in hot (375°) oil or Crisco until light brown, turning as you cook. Makes about 2 dozen doughnuts.

title: hilda's biscuits(baking powder)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix dry ingredients well in a bowl.
Cut in Crisco with pastry blender until mixture looks like meal.
Stir in milk.
Add enough milk to make a soft puffy dough easy to roll out.
Knead lightly (about 6 times).
Cut into circles with cookie cutter or glass.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Add sugar to cream; whip until stiff.
Add cake crumbs, strawberries and coconut.
Fold in gently, but thoroughly.
Spoon into dessert dishes and chill for several hours before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix cream cheese, lemon juice, vanilla, sugar and egg yolk until creamy.
(I use electric beater.)

title: taco rice skillet
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, drain.
Reserve juice from tomatoes, adding enough water to make 2 1/2 cups.
Chop tomatoes and add to ground beef, along with taco seasoning, rice and water/tomato juice.
Stir.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes until most of liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Cover with grated Cheddar cheese.
Cover skillet again until cheese is melted.

title: turkish tacos
directions: Saute chopped onions in hot cooking oil until clear and brown. Add ground meat and cook until brown.
Mix in the taco seasoning mix, taco sauce and tomato paste.
Add salt, pepper or other spices (e.g. cumin) to taste and simmer until it makes a tasty sauce.
Serve by putting the meat in the separated pocket bread and add layers of lettuce, cheese and tomato cubes.
Make it hotter by adding Mexican style salsa sauce as you prefer.

title: welch rabbit
directions: Melt butter and cheese in double boiler.
Beat in eggs, mustard, salt, pepper and milk.
Cook until smooth.
Serve over crackers.

title: southern chicken & dumplings
directions: Clean chicken, cut into serving pieces, place in a pot. Cover with water, add onion, salt, pepper and cook until tender, about 2 1/2 or 3 hours.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and parsley.
Add milk to make a thick batter.
Drop from a spoon into boiling chicken broth.
Cook about 20 minutes without raising lid. Place chicken on a platter and put dumplings around it.
Serves 6.

title: flank steak marinade
directions: Put flank steak in shallow baking dish.
(Do this marinade the night before or at least 6 to 8 hours before serving time.)
Pour over steak.
Turn steak frequently as it marinates to tenderize the meat.
Grill quickly each side (approximately 3 minutes), then cut at an angle, not straight, for tender slices.

title: onion baked fish
directions: Salt fish. Mix sour cream and mayonnaise with dressing mix. Dip fish in mixture and roll in crushed onion rings. Spray baking pan or dish. Arrange fish, single layer. Bake
20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: sunshine rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss well, but lightly, together. Place in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake in a slow oven (325°) for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually beat in sugar a little at a time.
Continue beating until very stiff and glossy. Cover pie completely, being sure to cover all edges, touching the crust.
Brown lightly.

title: cinnamon stars
directions: Lightly grease two cookie sheets.
Beat the egg whites until stiff peaks are formed.
Gradually add, beating constantly, the confectioners sugar.
Beat egg white-sugar mixture for 5 minutes with an electric mixer on medium speed.
Blend in lemon peel and cinnamon.
Set aside 1/2 cup of this meringue mixture and fold almonds into remaining meringue mixture.
Gently pat or roll out 3/8-inch thick on canvas sprinkled with granulated sugar.
Lightly sprinkle the top of the dough with more sugar.
Cut out cookies with 2 to 2 1/2-inch star-shaped cookie cutter, dipped in confectioners sugar.
Carefully place stars on cookie sheets.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon of the reserved meringue onto each cookie, drawing meringue out onto points of the star.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes.
With a spatula, immediately remove cookies from cookie sheets to cooling racks.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Sift baking powder with flour.
Then alternately add milk and flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt cake pan at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter in microwave for 2 minutes.
Add powdered sugar and graham crackers.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and shortening in microwave for 3 minutes.
Pour frosting over other mixture and refrigerate to harden.
Or stir all ingredients together.

title: farmhouse barbecue muffins
directions: Separate dough and flatten to 5-inch circle.
Press into bottom and up the sides of a greased muffin cup pan; set aside. In skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
In small bowl, mix ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar and chili powder; stir smooth.
Add meat mixture well.
Divide among muffin cups, about 1/4 cup each. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes at 375°, until golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes.
Yields 10.

title: chocolate malt cake
directions: Melt chocolate and cool. Cream the butter and sugar.
Sift and measure the flour.
Add chocolate to sugar and butter.
Add beaten egg yolks. Add flour and milk alternately.
Add nuts and vanilla. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: grandma's nut crescents(a special family recipe)
directions: Cream the cheese and oleo together; add flour.
Mix by hand. Form balls size of walnuts.
Chill overnight.
Roll out in powdered sugar.
Combine egg, nuts, sugar and just enough milk to make it easy to spread.
Spread and roll up.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Can also use cinnamon or jelly filling.

title: macaroni salad
directions: In mixing bowl, combine macaroni, onions, bell pepper, pickles, celery seed and eggs; toss well. Stir in enough mayonnaise and mustard to hold mixture together.
May be chilled before serving.

title: saucy beef and bean dish
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes or until heated through. Makes 6 (1-cup) servings.

title: quick and easy punch
directions: Place sherbet ice cream in punch bowl.
Pour Sprite over ice cream and allow to melt slightly.
Add ginger ale at the last minute.
Serve immediately.

title: children's delight casserole
directions: Mix wieners, milk and soups together, adding cooked noodles or macaroni.
Stir together and bake in a 1-quart casserole dish for 25 minutes at 375°.
Cool and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.
Serve with dinner rolls.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan in 350° oven. Mix flour, sugar and milk in bowl and pour over butter. (Do Not Stir.) Pour blueberries over flour mixture and bake for 30 to 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Mix 1/2 jello, pineapple, water and Port wine.
Chill until firm.
Mix walnuts, celery, cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread on jello that is already firm.
Add remaining jello on top of last layer.
Chill and garnish with grapes.

title: squash relish
directions: Add
squash
mixture
and bring to a boil again.
Spoon into jars and seal.
Makes 5 to 6 pints.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and sift.
Stir in oil, eggs, buttermilk and prunes.
Mix well.
Bake in an 8 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm and add topping.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs, then add dry ingredients.
Add strawberries and pecans last.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake pie crust for 10 minutes.
Turn temperature down to 350°.
Brown the ground beef, onions and seasoning according to package.
In a bowl, combine refried beans and salsa.
Take 1/2 the refried beans mixture and put in the bottom of the pie crust; then put 1/2 the ground beef and 1/2 the cheese.
Then repeat with the rest of the ingredients.
Bake on cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes.
Garnish with lettuce, tomato and black olives.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix with soup.
Sprinkle onion rings on top.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes, until onion rings are crisp and brown.

title: mary's pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, flour, sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, allspice, butter, salt, milk and Carnation milk.
Add whole eggs and beaten egg whites added last.
This makes a very large pie or two small ones.

title: any fruit cobbler
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and pour in about an 8 x 11-inch pan.
Add fruit until it's about 1/2-inch from top of pan. Place in oven and cook at 350° until brown and center is not runny.
This may be doubled, if necessary.
Great topped with ice cream.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into 1/2-inch pieces and cook until barely tender (lightly salted).
Drain.
Lightly saute chopped onion.
Mix ingredients 1 through 7 and place in 1 1/2 quart casserole dish (oiled).
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven about 35 minutes.
This is a very popular covered dish item.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix like pie dough:
butter, powdered sugar and flour.
Put in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Beat together lemon juice, baking powder, lemon rind, eggs, sugar, salt and 2 tablespoons flour; pour over crust.
Bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine, vanilla and sugar; shape into balls.
Place on cookie sheet with wax paper; refrigerate.
Melt chocolate and shortening.
Dip peanut butter balls into chocolate and pack on wax paper.

title: betty's orange ginger cookies(my favorite!)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and syrup.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well; add orange peel.
Roll into small balls.
Flatten with glass (I roll mine in sugar).
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Mound apples in buttered 9-inch pie plate; sprinkle with orange juice.
Combine sugar, flour, spices and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until the apples are tender and topping is crisp.
Serve warm with whipped cream if desired.

title: hard candies
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water to medium crack stage (295°). Stir in flavoring extract or oil, salt and coloring.
Quickly pour onto a sheet of aluminum foil.
When cooled, crack into pieces with knife handle.
Store in tightly covered container. Yields 1 pound.

title: nip's mincemeat
directions: First shoot your deer.
Boil down the neck and, when reasonably tender, pick the meat from the bones and put it through a food processor or grinder.

To 2 quarts of the ground meat and 2 quarts of the meat juices, add the remaining ingredients and simmer about 3 hours, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking. Pack into quart jars and can in a pressure canner at 10 pounds pressure for 20 minutes.
May also be frozen.
Yields 7 to 8 quarts.

title: fourteen day sweet pickles
directions: Mix 2 cups of canning salt to 1 gallon water.
Mix well. Slice cucumbers, pack in jars, and pour salt water on cucumbers. Soak 7 days.
Pour off salt water, take pickles out of jars, and rinse twice.
Eighth day return to jars.
Pour boiling water to cover pickles.
Soak 24 hours, pour off water.
Mix alum to one gallon of water.
Mix well.
Pour over pickles.
Next day pour off water.
Take out of jars and rinse well.
Return to jars, and make syrup on 10th day.
To make syrup, mix 7 c. sugar, 2 c. apple cider vinegar, and 2 Tbsp. pickling spice, put in cheese cloth, and boil.
Pour over pickles in jars.
Then reboil syrup, and pour over pickles in jars.
The 11th, 12th, 13th, and 14th day.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Sift together and add soda, flour, salt, ginger and cinnamon.
Chill, if necessary. Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Dip top in granulated sugar.
Place sugared side up on a greased cookie sheet.
Do not press down.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 4 dozen.

title: company gumbo
directions: Cook duck and chicken in water to cover in large stockpot, just until meat is cooked; do not overcook.
Drain well.
Add flour to hot oil in stockpot over medium heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, to form caramel-colored roux; do not burn.
Add duck, chicken, sausage, vegetables, tomato sauce and paste and seasonings to roux.
Cook, stirring frequently, for 8 to 9 minutes or until vegetables begin to soften.
Reduce heat and add broth. Prepare rice according to package directions.
Serve 1 cup gumbo over 1 cup cooked rice.
Serves 12.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Crumble graham crackers and mix with hands and all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Press down in Bundt pan.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for at least one week.

title: energy bars
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour out in large pan or plate. Cut into pieces.
Makes about 25 pieces.
If you prefer, mixture may be rolled into balls.
Chill before serving to blend flavors.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Bring fruit to a boil; add dry jello.
Mix and cool.
Beat cream cheese, Dream Whip and milk.
Mix well.
Add to cold fruit and jello.
Refrigerate.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Place butter in an 8-inch round glass baking dish.
Microwave at High 30 seconds to melt.
Stir in brown sugar; spread evenly in dish.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Arrange pineapple slices over sugar-butter mixture.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over pineapple slices.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions, using the pineapple juice for the liquid.
Pour batter over the pineapple slices.
Microwave at High 5 to 7 minutes; rotate dish 1/4 turn after 3 minutes of microwaving.
Place cake on counter; let stand 5 minutes before removing from baking dish.

title: maggie's shepherd's pie
directions: Fry onion until clear.
Add hamburger meat and brown.
Drain off fat.
Add water to cover.
Add bay leaf and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
In the meantime, peel, boil and mash potatoes.
Pour hamburger mixture into 4-quart casserole dish.
Add frozen peas.
Top mixture with mashed potatoes.
Put in oven at 350° until top of potatoes are brown (20 minutes or so).
Serve with Brussels sprouts on the side.

title: "old florida footprint" black bean soup
directions: Wash beans and check for stones.
Soak overnight in a regular-size crock-pot (or equivalent size pot).
Do not drain. Add remaining ingredients, place on low heat and cook all day. Stir occasionally. Remove salt pork before serving.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine undiluted soup, peas with liquid, pimento, onion and Worcestershire sauce in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Fold tuna and cheese into mixture in casserole dish.
Arrange onion rings around edge.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 25 minutes.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Combine crab meat, horseradish, salt, lemon juice and pepper. Fold in yogurt.
Cover; chill.

title: rum raisin sauce(for ice cream)
directions: Pour rum over raisins to plump.
Set aside.
In heavy saucepan, mix sugar and water.
Add cinnamon stick.
Bring to a boil and boil hard for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add raisins and rum and cook for 5 minutes more.
Add vanilla, lemon rind, orange rind and pecans.
Spoon in sterilized jar and seal or store covered in refrigerator.
Great on ice cream or pound cake!

title: vegetable dip
directions: Cream together first 2 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Serve with favorite vegetables.

title: chipped beef bread dip
directions: Soak beef in cold water for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Chop finely. Add all other ingredients and refrigerate.
Cut out center of Vienna bread and line with aluminum foil.
Fill with dip and sprinkle with parsley.

title: peanut butter "stuff"
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and flavoring.
Pour over corn flakes and peanuts and mix until cereal is coated.
Pour into pan while still warm.
Cut into squares.

title: cletah's oriental salad
directions: Simmer chicken in water until done; cut into bite size pieces. Brown almonds and sesame seed on baking sheet in 350° oven until light brown.
Tear lettuce into small pieces.
Chop green onions. Slice wontons into 3 sections and deep fry in peanut oil until lightly browned.
Lightly toss all ingredients together in large bowl.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and mix lightly to coat (dressing recipe follows).

title: blueberry buttermilk muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a mixing bowl; set aside.
Combine egg, buttermilk and butter; mix well.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients; pour in liquid ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy mexican dinner
directions: Cook meat and onions.
Stir in noodles, tomatoes, tomato paste and 1 cup cheese, olives and seasonings.
Put in 2-quart casserole, top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal sliced cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and oats.
Mix thoroughly.
(Dough will be stiff.)
Shape into rolls 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Chill if necessary.
Slice 3/8-inch thick and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.*
These are a shortbread-like cookie.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together in medium sized bowl until smooth.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until center is set.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Add grated squash and stir to combine.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add raisins and nuts to dry ingredients, then stir into zucchini mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix in saucepan the margarine, milk and cocoa.
Heat until it boils.
Pour hot into powdered sugar.
Mix in a large bowl.
Add vanilla.
Spread on warm or cold cake.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package with 3 eggs, 1/3 cup oil and substituted reserved pineapple juice plus added water to make required amount of liquid (1 1/4 cups).
Add drained, crushed pineapple.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes. After baking, while hot, make holes with toothpick in cake (plenty of them).
Pour pina colada mix on and spread.
Let cool.
Add Cool Whip (as icing) and cover with coconut.
Keep refrigerated. (Longer it sits, better it gets, but won't last.)

title: jello salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill for 2 to 3 hours and serve.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Peel and grate sweet potatoes. Cream sugar and eggs; add other ingredients.
Mix all ingredients and place in a buttered baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: raspberry romanoff
directions: Reserve five berries for garnish.
Mix remaining berries, sugar and liqueur.
Cover and refrigerate for two hours, stirring occasionally.
Just before serving, mix whipped topping and ice cream.
Fold into berry mixture.
Garnish with berries.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook the chicken, but save the broth.
Let the chicken cool, then debone it.
Cook rice with broth until ready.
Combine chicken, celery, onion, carrot, spices and spaghetti sauce.
Let it cook until ready.
Add rice and stir well.
Enjoy it!

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the bread crumbs. Sprinkle bread on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: wild rice chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken in apple juice until tender.
Dice chicken and chill.
Gently toss together chicken, wild rice, grapes, apples, celery and 1/2 of the almonds.
Mix the dressing and add to the chicken mixture and toss lightly.
When ready to serve place remaining slivered almonds over the top.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can of onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake uncovered for 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender on top of stove.
Place cooked rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Put chicken breast on top of rice, then add both cans of soup (no water) and 1 1/2 cans of chicken broth from chicken.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: First Layer:
Melt margarine; cool.
Add flour, nuts and brown sugar.
Press into 10 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add other ingredients and refrigerate until Jell-O sets.

title: easy cookies(peanut butter)
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Make crisscross pattern on cookies, using floured fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: santa fe chili
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight.
Cook slowly until done.
Brown meat in fat.
Add beans and enough water to make 1 cup liquid. Add rest of ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook the macaroni; set aside and let cool.
Then put a layer of macaroni in a baking dish.
Add layer of tuna, mushroom soup and onion.
Repeat layers again.
Place cheese on top and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: herbed salmon on the grill
directions: In large glass bowl, combine dressing, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, dill weed, chives and lemon pepper.
Add steaks and turn to coat evenly.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 1 hour.
Drain steaks, reserving liquid.
Place steaks in oiled grill basket and grill 4 to 5 minutes per side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Brush steaks with marinade during grilling.

title: chili (with beans)
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add to other ingredients and cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: date pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and butter until fluffy; add crumbs and two-thirds of milk and let soak.
Add chopped dates, nuts, rest of milk and vanilla.
Add baking powder last.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Add lemon juice, green onions, corned beef and mayonnaise.
Mix all together well.
Roll into ball.
Cover with chopped nuts and refrigerate.
Will keep 4 to 5 days.
Serve with crackers.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions and bake in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Boil 1 cup sugar and 1 cup evaporated milk in saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in the marshmallows, coconut and pecans.
Pour over warm cake.
Bring 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1/2 cup evaporated milk and butter to a boil.
Stir in chocolate chips to melt. Spread over cake.
It is very important to use the right size pan.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Brown turkey and drain.
In large bowl, combine turkey, vegetables, soup, onions and salt and pepper.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart baking pan or casserole bowl.
Layer biscuits across top. Bake at 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven until bubbly and golden brown.

title: jello salad
directions: Bring pineapple juice to a boil.
Stir in Jell-O and let set until it starts to congeal.
Stir in all ingredients and fold in whipped cream.
Congeal.

title: biscuit mix for waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture is as fine as corn meal.
Store in a tightly covered container in refrigerator.
Keeps well.
Can also be used for pancakes.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes and cut, unpeeled, into 1/4-inch thick slices. Drain on paper towel.
Combine flour, salt, sugar and pepper and dust tomato slices.
Add milk to the remaining flour mixture to make a thick batter.
Dip floured slices in batter and fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown ground turkey until cooked.
Drain, add tomato soup, red beans (undrained); cook for approximately 1/2 hour.

title: microwave pasta in a hurry
directions: Place chicken in 9-inch pie plate, cover with wax paper and microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes or until meat is no longer pink. Cool.
Cut in strips.

title: squash casserole
directions: Put squash, onion, carrot and salt in pan.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Drain vegetables.
Put into bowl while vegetables are still hot.
Add margarine, soup and sour cream; mix well, then add 1 cup of stuffing mix, grated cheese and the package of seasoning that is with the stuffing.
Mix well; pour into greased casserole.
Top with rest of stuffing.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: no-fry zesty chicken cutlets
directions: Lay chicken cutlets flat on counter top.
Moderately tenderize cutlets with meat tenderizer.
Pour 2 cups Italian salad dressing into medium bowl.
Put cutlets in salad dressing, being sure they are fully immersed.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Pour bread crumbs onto flat surface.
Spray baking pan with baking spray.
Coat each cutlet with bread crumbs.
Lay in baking pan. Set oven to 325° and bake 20 minutes, turning until brown on each side.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
When ready to serve, pour juices over one tray of ice cubes in punch bowl.
Garnish with oranges.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix together first three ingredients and pat into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Beat together next three ingredients and pour over cake mixture; sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; cool, then refrigerate.
When cool, cut in small pieces.
Very rich.

title: boston sugar cookies
directions: Cream white sugar, brown sugar and Crisco with a mixer.
Beat eggs in well until fluffy.
Add almond extract, coconut extract and cream of tartar and beat well.
Beat in soda and flour.
This dough will be very stiff.
Chill dough overnight.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on a rack.
Makes 50 to 60 cookies.

title: sloppy joe's hamburger
directions: Brown onion and meat in skillet.
Add mustard and soup and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve on toasted hamburger buns.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sauerbraten(sour beef)
directions: Marinate beef cubes, vinegar and onions overnight.
Put all spices in a cloth bag and add to beef mixture. Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender. Remove and discard spices and onions. Remove meat and strain liquid.
Add sugar to liquid.
Crush gingersnaps to powder.
Slowly stir gingersnap powder into liquid to thicken to creamy texture.
Return meat to gravy and simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and milk.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Spoon out with a teaspoon. Makes 4 dozen.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Place mushrooms in container.
Combine rest of ingredients. Pour over mushrooms.
Refrigerate for at least 3 or 4 days before using.

title: beef stew
directions: Place
stew
in
2-quart Pyrex dish.
Put onion soup on top; pour soup and water over stew and onion soup.
Cover with foil and bake
at 300° for 3 hours.
Serve over rice, noodles or potatoes.

title: tomato jam
directions: Peel tomatoes.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add sugar; cook 20 minutes. Add Jell-O.
Cook 20 minutes.
Put in jars.
Seal with wax or regular Mason lids.

title: green chili salsa
directions: Chop or pulse on food processor chilies and onion.
Add tomatoes (can add more tomatoes if chilies are too hot) that have been pulsed a little.
Add garlic and spices.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Debone chicken.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix 1 can soup and 1/2 cup water.
Spread over chicken.
Mix flour, milk and margarine.
Pour over soup.
Pour broth over all. Bake at 350° until brown (about 45 minutes).

title: potato candy
directions: Wash potato with peeling still on. Boil in water until potato is done. Peel potato and mash it with a fork and add flavoring. While the potato is still hot/warm start adding in the powdered sugar and blend. It depends on how big the potato is as to how much powdered sugar you will use. It usually takes more than a box. (It reminds me of making dough.) You will need to work fast while the potato is still warm so that the powdered sugar will mix with the potato. Put the mixture on a piece of wax paper and flatten (just like rolling dough to make biscuits). You will then spread peanut butter on the flattened mixture and then roll it like a pen wheel. I make mine long and not as wide (if it is too wide it will not roll very well). Then you need to refrigerate for a couple of hours. Then slice and serve.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix meat, rice, onion and spices.
Form into 24 meatballs. Place in baking dish.
Add soup, tomato sauce and water (add more water if necessary).
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix 1 cup of sugar (reserve 1/2 cup for meringue) with cornstarch and spices.
Beat one egg and three egg yolks.
Add eggs to sour cream.
Mix with sugar mixture.
Mix together and add raisins.
Cook in double boiler until thick, stirring constantly. Pour into baked 9-inch crust.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Beat eggs, oil and milk, then add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake 15 minutes in 400° oven.
This batter can be stored in refrigerator for six weeks, covered.

title: brandy sauce
directions: Combine tapioca, sugar, salt and water in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Beat the egg until light and foamy.
Add the hot mixture to the egg, stirring well.
Return to the saucepan and place over low heat.
Cook and stir for 3 minutes but not allow the mixture to boil.
Remove from the heat and stir in the butter and brandy. Cool stirring once after 20 minutes.
This is real good over plain pound cake, fruit cake, or plum pudding.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Add sugar, vanilla flavoring and baking powder; beat again until stiff.
Fold in pecans and Ritz crackers. Put in greased pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Let cool. Top with Cool Whip.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, milk and eggs.
Cook until very thick. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, butter and the 2 tablespoons brown sugar.
Let cool.
Pour in a baked pie shell.
Add meringue.
Bake in a 400° oven until brown.

title: pink lemonade
directions: Fill the glass half full of cold water.
Put the lemon juice and sugar into the glass.
Stir slowly.
Put 3 ice cubes in the glass.
Slowly pour cranberry juice into glass until it is almost full.
Stir again.
Makes 1 serving.

title: stuffed spud soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, half and half and thawed potatoes.
Stir in cheese and heat gently.
Garnish and serve. Serves 8 to 10.

title: catfish cakes
directions: Poach and flake fish.
Add remaining ingredients, except cracker crumbs and shape into patties.
Coat with cracker crumbs and fry.

title: junior mint brownies
directions: For one 17 1/2 x 11-inch baking pan, 48 brownies, you will need:

title: candied walnuts
directions: In
2-quart saucepan, mix first 4 ingredients.	Cook to soft ball stage (238°).	Add walnuts and peppermint flavoring; stir until
creamy.
Quickly
turn
out	on
waxed
paper
and separate with forks.

title: baked blueberry shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix blueberries, 1/4 cup apple juice concentrate and 2 tablespoons fructose.
Spread fruit mixture in a 9 x 9-inch pan and set aside.
In a medium bowl, mix 1/2 cup apple juice concentrate, 1/4 cup fructose, oil and egg.
Blend well. Add vanilla.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to batter.
Pour batter over blueberry mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: cranberry sauce mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
In another bowl, combine cranberry sauce and applesauce.
Combine two mixtures in a mold. Chill.
Serve on a bed of lettuce leaves.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain juice from can peaches.
Combine apple and peaches in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut up in the fruit.
Sprinkle coconut over the complete fruit (optional). Melt margarine over low heat to prevent burning.
Pour margarine over cake mix.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool completely.
Cut in squares.
Serve upside down, topped with spoonful of Cool Whip.

title: coconut ice box cake
directions: Mix sugar, Cool Whip, sour cream and coconut in bowl.
Cover and let sit overnight.
Second day, mix and bake cake according to package directions.
Bake in 9-inch round pans, greased and floured (2 or 3).
Let cool.
Spread frosting generously between layers and over top and sides of cake.
Refrigerate.
Will keep one week.

title: lemon dill mustard
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in sterilized jars and store in a cool,
dark place.

title: bologna jumbo roll-ups
directions: Blend and mix well all ingredients.
Spread mixture on meat slices.
Roll tightly.
Wrap in wax paper and chill.
Cut into thin slices and serve on toothpicks.
May be dipped into cocktail or horseradish sauce.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Bake in a large casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°. Sprinkle on the cheese the last 10 minutes.

title: flan
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease six (6 ounce) custard cups.
In a small skillet, over medium heat, heat 1/3 cup of sugar until it turns to golden brown color, stirring constantly.
Pour sugar syrup into bottom of prepared custard cups.
In a large bowl, beat eggs, salt and remaining 1/3 cup sugar at medium speed.
Gradually beat in milk and vanilla.
Pour mixture evenly over sugar syrup in cups. Place cups in 13 x 19-inch baking pan.
Pour enough hot water in pan to come halfway up sides of custard cups.
Bake for 50 minutes. Refrigerate until well chilled.
Loosen custard from sides of cups with knife.
Invert onto dessert dishes, letting syrup run down.

title: never-fail divinity
directions: Combine water, sugar and salt. Bring to rolling boil. Boil for 2 minutes only. Place marshmallow cream in bowl and pour hot syrup over it. Stir well until candy holds shape. Add nuts. Working very fast, drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper. Cool. Good, good, good! Makes 28 to 30 pieces.

title: crunchy peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat together the peanut butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla and beat again.
Add flour; stir and then add the peanuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls on an ungreased baking sheet.
With a fork make a cross pattern on each cookie.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 15 to 18 minutes or until very lightly browned.
Makes 16 to 24 cookies.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl, beat shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Gradually add to shortening mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in mincemeat.
Drop by spoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in plate.
In blender, beat remaining ingredients 15 seconds on high or 1 minute with hand beater until smooth. Pour into pie plate.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and eggs until well blended.
Spread on a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix cheese, eggs and sugar until smooth.
Pour over cake mix mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: honey bread
directions: Beat honey,
milk
and	brown sugar until well blended. Mix together dry
ingredients
and add to honey mixture.
Pour into a well
greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan and bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours, or until it tests done with a toothpick.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Gradually add sugar, beating well on medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine buttermilk and soda. Stir until soda dissolves.
Add flour to butter mixture alternately with buttermilk mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, walnuts and coconut, stirring well.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) with cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Fold gently into batter.

title: pot roast
directions: Rub seasoning into roast.
Rub flour over roast, covering all surfaces.
Braze meat in hot oil in heavy skillet.
Place meat in slow cooker.
Add vegetables and water.
Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: 1-2-3 spaghetti
directions: Brown meat in large skillet on medium-high heat; drain.
Add spaghetti and soup; toss lightly.
Microwave process cheese spread as directed on label.
Stir into spaghetti mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: emergency paint
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.

title: linguine with tuna sauce
directions: In large skillet, saute onion, pepper, garlic, lemon juice, basil and red pepper flakes in oil until soft.
Add tomatoes and 1/4 cup white wine (dry); bring to boil.
Simmer, uncovered.
Cook linguine to package directions.
Add tuna to sauce in skillet. Cook until heated through, about 15 minutes.
Drain pasta.
Toss with sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cabbage salad or slaw
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in a large container that will seal.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Mix pumpkin, eggs, sugar, evaporated milk, salt and pumpkin pie spice and pour into a greased 9 x 15-inch pan.
Top with spice cake mix.
Drizzle melted butter and sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and then add 1/2 cup fruit juice, alternately with dry ingredients.
Last add fruit and nuts which have been rolled in extra 1/2 cup flour.
Bake in slow oven about 200° for about 4 hours.

title: wild rice and pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients.
Bake with lid for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Check 30 minutes before being done, if it looks dry, add a little water.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl.
Pour into melted butter and stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender; drain. Combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables and salt.
Blend soup and milk; heat through.
Add cheese; heat and stir until cheese melts.
Add to noodle mixture.
Turn into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with toasted almonds.
Bake uncovered in hot oven (425°) for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix the ingredients into 3/4-inch balls.
Cook in canola oil or vegetable oil at 350° to 375°.
You will need at least 2 inches of oil as balls will float.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and fructose. Beat in egg, water and vanilla. Combine flour, baking soda and salt in sifter. Sift dry ingredients into creamed mixture, stirring to blend thoroughly. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet about 2-inches apart. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 30 cookies.

title: japanese noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and toss with olive oil in a bowl.
When cooled, add remaining ingredients. Chill overnight.

title: cornish game hens\(serves 2)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart pan, melt 1/2 stick oleo.
Add rice, celery and onions.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer over low heat 20 minutes (until rice is fluffy).
Add mushrooms; cool.
Toss cheese over cooled rice mixture.
Season hens inside with salt and pepper. Butter inside of hens.
Stuff with rice mixture.
Place on a rack, breast side up, in shallow baking dish; baste with butter.
Loosely cover with foil.
Roast in preheated oven at 400° for 30 minutes. Remove foil and continue roasting for 45 minutes.

title: deep dish chili
directions: Brown ground beef and combine with remaining ingredients, except corn muffin mix.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Spoon corn muffin mix over hot chili; bake for 10 minutes on one side.
Turn corn mix and bake 10 more minutes.
You can also make the muffins separately and just bake the chili for 20 minutes.

title: blue ribbon pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Stir in flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; then reduce heat to 325° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: brown bread
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Beat in eggs and buttermilk.
Mix in salt, baking soda, flour and molasses.
Add raisins if wanted. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: aunt juanita's lasagna
directions: Brown sausage.
Brown meat with onion and garlic powder. Combine meats with tomatoes, sauce, water and spices.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Remove sausage and slice.
Cook noodles.
Layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan, alternating sauce, noodles and cheese.
Top with sausage, then cover with sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chocolate cookie cake and icing
directions: Place flour, soda and sugar in medium mixing bowl.
In a saucepan, mix chocolate syrup, water, Crisco and butter.
When saucepan ingredients have come to a boil, slowly pour over the dry ingredients and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 16 x 11-inch pan and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. While cake is still warm, poke holes with a fork, cake tester, toothpick, etc., and pour icing over the cake.
Freezes nicely. Cut serving pieces small as cake is pretty rich.

title: breakfast sausage sandwiches
directions: Spread margarine on one side of bread.
Place 4 slices, buttered side down, in a lightly greased baking dish.
Put sausage on top of bread.
Top with 4 slices of bread, buttered side up. Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over sandwiches.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Remove from refrigerator; let stand 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Blend in blender until thick. Serve chilled in elegant glasses.
Serves 6.

title: pasta
directions: Microwave:
Combine cream, basil, salt and pepper in 4-quart glass measure.
Place in microwave; cook on medium (50% power) 15 minutes or until mixture is thickened and slightly reduced. Remove from oven.
Stir in 1/2 cup pistachios and set aside.

title: tuna noodle crisp
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package, drain.
Melt Crisco in large skillet, add onion and green pepper and cook until tender.
Stir in soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Add cooked noodles and tuna.
Place mixture in a 1 1/2 or 2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs or crumbled regular potato chips on top.
Bake in 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes.

title: turnip stuffing
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs, parsley, thyme, sage, pepper and salt.
Add bread cubes and apple chunks.
Toss until thoroughly combined.
In large skillet, melt 3/4 cup butter over medium heat. Saute mushrooms and onions until tender.
Add to bread crumb mixture.
Toss again.

title: skillet barbecue
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in other ingredients. Add meat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: apricot upside-down cake
directions: Melt brown sugar and butter in a large iron skillet. Blend until smooth.
Remove from heat as soon as it begins to bubble. Over this mixture, place apricots, round side down.
Mix the sugar, egg yolks, flour, baking powder, water, salt and vanilla together and pour over apricots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let stand in skillet a short while before turning upside down on large plate.

title: beef and potato puff
directions: Brown meat in salad oil.
Drain.
Stir in gravy mix, water, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Prepare potatoes as directed.
Stir in nutmeg and cheese to potato mixture.
Pour beef mixture into casserole dish or baking pan (9 x 9-inch); spoon the potato mixture evenly over beef.
Sprinkle top with a little paprika if desired.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Insert toothpick to see if done.
Cool and frost.
Very moist!

title: tuna and rice
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet on medium high heat.
Add onion.
Cook and stir until tender but not browned.
Stir in vegetables, milk, soup and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in tuna, rice and parsley.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Garnish with almonds.

title: macaroon chewies
directions: Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Beat together egg whites and salt until stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar until stiff shiny peaks.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Drop by tablespoons 2 inches apart on prepared cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cool on cookie sheets for a few minutes, then cool completely on wire racks.
Store tightly in a covered dish.

title: peanut butter-caramel crunch
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter together.
Add corn flakes. Spoon out on cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Enjoy.

title: russian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Catsup may be used in this.

title: baked chicken
directions: Pour 1 cup Good Seasons honey mustard dressing over 2 1/2 pounds chicken (dressing should be prepared) in large bowl. Refrigerate and marinate at least 3 hours.
Remove chicken from marinade.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is done. Baste once with marinade.

title: beef parmigiana
directions: Place meat between pieces of wax paper larger than the meat and lay on a board; pound meat thin (about 1/4 inch) with a heavy skillet or rolling pin trim off gristle and excess fat.
Cut into 5 or 8 pieces.
Dip meat in egg; roll in mixture of Parmesan cheese and crumbs.
Heat oil in large skillet; brown steak on both sides over medium heat until golden brown.
Lay in shallow, wide baking dish.

In same skillet cook onion over low heat until soft; stir in salt, pepper, sugar, marjoram and tomato paste, gradually add hot water, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes scraping browned bits from pan; pour most of the sauce over meat.
Top with slices of mozzarella cheese and remaining sauce.
Bake in moderate oven 350° for about 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Makes 4 - 6 servings.

title: texas-style chili
directions: In a large saucepan over med-high heat, cook beef, chili powder, cumin, salt and garlic powder until beef is browned, stirring to separate meat. Pour off fat. Add flour and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually stir in water and picante sauce. Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat to low. Cook 15 minutes stirring occasionally. Serve with onions, cheese, cilantro and additional picante sauce.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain grease.
Put in bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Layer cheese, cut up on top of meat.
Blend milk, eggs and Bisquick.
Pour over top of meat and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: tomato soup salad
directions: Heat the soup, then add the lemon jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients; stir together and chill until set.

title: caramel apples
directions: Wash, dry, and cut apples into wedges.
Melt caramels, and cream together in microwave oven or over hot water.
Cool, and dip apples in caramel.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Boil until syrup mixture spins a 12-inch thread.
Pour 1/2 mixture over egg whites (in thin stream), beating constantly.
Boil remaining mixture 2 to 3 minutes.
Add to egg white mixture in stream.
Beat until candy loses gloss.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding flour gradually.
Beat on high for five minutes.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Not done?
Bake at 350° until done.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Heat oven to 400° and grease 10 x 1-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese in dish.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth and pour into dish over mixture.
Bake until knife comes out clean when inserted in middle, approximately 20 minutes.
Can add chopped celery, mango, hot pepper or oregano for some spice.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Chop tomato, bell pepper, onion and cucumber. Combine all ingredients. Serve with crackers.

title: ginger baked beans
directions: In large-holed colander, drain most of can liquid from pork and beans.
Pour beans
into baking dish and add onion, green pepper and tomato; mix gently.
In small bowl, combine brown sugar and Vernors and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour evenly over bean mixture and bake at 350° until bubbly.
If flat open dish is used, bake
about 35 minutes; if bean pot, uncovered, is used, bake about 2 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Boil and prepare potatoes for mashing, seasoned with butter and milk.
In large skillet, brown beef at medium heat and drain. Add vegetable soup and simmer until juice has been soaked into beef.
Place in baking dish and spread mashed potatoes over top. Place in preheated oven until potatoes are lightly brown.
Oven temperature, 350°.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and celery; cook until tender. Stir in tomatoes and tomato paste.
Season with sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Combine with butter, Parmesan and eggs; mix well.
Line 2 greased pie plates with spaghetti mixture to form crust.
Spoon cottage cheese over crust.
Top with meat mixture and sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings per pie.

title: fish casserole
directions: Cut fish into good size pieces.
Dip each piece into mixture of flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Place fish into buttered baking dish.
In small bowl mix sour cream, Parmesan cheese and mushrooms.
Spread mixture over fish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hot pepper mustard
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook at slow boil for 1/2 hour. Seal in jars.
Makes 9 to 11 pints.

title: batter for fried vegetables
directions: Beat all ingredients by hand until well blended.
Prepare vegetables and dip into batter.
Fry in oil preheated to 375° until brown, salt lightly.
If vegetables are coated with flour before dipping in batter, the batter will stay on better when frying.
This batter can be used to coat whole okra, sliced onions, squash, eggplant and green tomatoes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix well peanut butter, cream cheese and sugar. Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip. Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours. Before serving, top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge meat in flour and brown in butter (add a little olive oil).
Remove meat.
Brown onions and mushrooms and cook 5 minutes. Add meat, tomato juice, sherry and broth and simmer 2 hours or until tender.
Add sour cream (just before serving) carefully so cream does not curdle.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: coffee mocha
directions: Mix together and store in airtight container.
Mix 2 to 3 teaspoons to your taste with cup of hot water or milk.

title: aunt marie's banana bread
directions: *To sour milk, combine 1 tablespoon vinegar and enough milk to measure 1/2 cup.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: In large saucepan combine hominy and onion, cook until no juice is left. Add chilies, margarine, garlic powder and sour cream. Mix well and pour into casserole dish. Cover with cheddar cheese and bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: whiskey balls
directions: Roll vanilla wafers to crumble.
Mix dry ingredients with the crumbs.
Then add the rum and bourbon and drip in the Karo.
Mix thoroughly and roll into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar and store carefully.
They improve with age, even as you and I!

title: chicken quickly
directions: Brown chicken lightly in oiled skillet.
Add other ingredients.
Cook, covered, until chicken is done (about 12 1/2 to 16 1/4 minutes).
