That's quickly, isn't it?

title: zucchini soup
directions: Saute onion in butter in 2-quart saucepan.
Add zucchini, chicken broth, nutmeg, basil, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until zucchini is well done.
Turn into blender bowl or food processor (in 2 batches) and process until pureed. Return to saucepan and stir in half and half.
Blend well.

title: grandma hoover's brown bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour in regular size vegetable cans (as molds for bread) and fill each 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Put cut up chicken in a
pot with oil. Cover very well so it will cook with steam on low heat for about 45 minutes.
Add vegetables, tomato sauce and 1 can of water. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes.
Boil the 3 cups water, butter and salt. When boiling, add the rice and cover for about 12 minutes on low heat. Serve rice under chicken or on the side.

title: pearlie's potato salad
directions: Cook until slightly thickened.
Add 1 pint Miracle Whip salad dressing and 1 1/2 tablespoons mustard.
Let cool.
Mix with potato mixture.
Chill before serving.

title: paul's popcorn
directions: Put popcorn in popper; pop until popped.
Butter and salt.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Sift flour and baking powder into bowl.
Add butter and mix well with fork.
Add cheese and milk, mixing until well blended. Knead on lightly floured board.
Roll into sticks, 7-inches long and 3/4-inch wide.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown in 350° oven.

title: grandma belle's raspberry tarts
directions: Cut out circles of pie crust and press into the very small size muffin pans.
Fill with raspberry jam.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 15 or 20 minutes or until crusts are nice and brown.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4-inches. Beat all ingredients until smooth (1 minute). Pour into plate. Bake until knife comes out clean, about 30 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Clean strawberries.
Line pie shell with 1 box of whole strawberries.
Mash the other box of strawberries and add cornstarch and sugar, then cook until thick.
Set aside to cool. Pour cooked strawberries over the whole strawberries.
Top with whipped cream.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: corn casserole
directions: In a saucepan over heat, make a smooth sauce with cream cheese, milk, butter and garlic salt. Remove from heat and stir in green chilies and corn. Pour in buttered 8 x 12-inch Pyrex casserole. Dot liberally with more butter. Bake until bubbly, about 30 minutes at 150°. You can also bake at 400° for 15 minutes. If you want more color, you can sprinkle grated cheese and/or paprika on top before baking.

title: clam chowder
directions: Chop the clams.
Melt the butter in a pan and add the onion, potato and water.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until the potato is tender.
Add clams; cook 3 minutes.
Add the milk and heat but don't boil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with crisp crackers.

title: nonfat cream soup mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in refrigerator in a quart jar.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch glass or metal pan, melt butter in oven. Sprinkle cracker crumbs, mix and press down.
Pour milk on top evenly.
Top with chocolate chips, then coconut, then nuts.
Press down.

title: aline's ham biscuits with swiss cheese
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and spread thin layer on ham biscuits. Top with cheese.
Add ham.
Heat through.

title: bubble bread
directions: Spray Bundt pan and flour to coat sides and bottom.
Place frozen rolls in pan.
Mix brown sugar and pudding mix; sprinkle over rolls.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over pudding mixture.
Spread pecans over this; pour melted butter over pecans. Place on cabinet overnight; do not cover.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Place the apple pie filling in dish. Sprinkle the sugar over the fruit. Dot with the butter.
Mix in another bowl the flour, 1 stick butter and brown sugar.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: corned beef and cabbage(serves 4)
directions: Cook vegetables in chicken stock until tender, about 45 minutes.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix soup and water.
Use Pyrex baker with layers of potatoes, onions, salt, pepper and soup.
(Save soup for top layer.)
Add cheese if desired.
Bake uncovered at least 1 1/2 hours in low oven (325°) to keep from separating until potatoes are done.
Use generous amount of pepper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine cheese, parsley and crumbs.
Set aside.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Melt butter in medium saucepan, adding garlic to flavor.
Dip each breast in butter and roll in crumbs.
In a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan, combine chicken broth, water and rice.
Place chicken on top.
Cover the pan with foil. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Take foil off for the last 10 minutes so the top can brown.

title: aunt nora's hot chicken salad
directions: Make sauce with flour, margarine and broth.
Add chicken and other ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Grease pan.
Line pan with 3/4 of the potato chips.
Pour the mixture over potato chips.
Top with remaining chips.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: For marinade, combine lime peel, lime juice, garlic, salt, oregano, cumin and hot pepper sauce in a shallow baking dish. Add chicken, peppers and onions.
Cover and chill for two hours, turning chicken once.

title: chocolate squares
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and baking soda.
Boil cocoa, water and oleo.
Pour boiled mixture over dry ingredients; mix well. Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat well again.
Bake in oiled jelly roll pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: white star cookies
directions: Melt stars and peanut butter.
Mix all ingredients together and drop on wax paper.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Dip meat in egg; roll in Parmesan cheese and crumbs.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Brown cutlets on both sides over medium heat until golden brown.
Lay in shallow baking dish.
In same skillet, cook onion until soft.
Stir in seasonings and tomato paste.
Add hot water and stir.
Pour most of sauce over meat; top with cheese and remaining sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Double sauce if served with spaghetti.

title: rocket burgers
directions: Mix together.
Roll in cylinder shape.
Wrap bacon around. Stick toothpick to hold ends of bacon.
Cook on barbecue grill.

title: best baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef. Rinse and drain. Add onion, mustard, catsup, sugar, salt and beans.
Cook in a large skillet on medium for 30 minutes.

title: jello base punch
directions: Mix water and sugar, boil 10 minutes.
Add gelatin, lemon juice and almond extract.
Cool to room temperature, then chill. Makes 5 quarts.

title: saltine cracker crunch candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in large saucepan.
Bring to full boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, coconut, crackers and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into buttered pan and chill.
Cut into squares.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.
This is good candy and very easy to make.

title: zucchini soup(low calorie)
directions: Add sliced zucchini in combined water and bouillon cubes in saucepan.
Heat until zucchini is tender.
Pour mixture into blender or food processor and puree.
Return pureed mixture to pan and add milk.
Heat to serving temperature.
Serves 4.

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Mix cereal, sugar, flour, salt and soda.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Store in covered bowl in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.
When ready to cook, grease muffin tins.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake about 20 minutes.

title: helen's baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper in skillet.
Mix all other ingredients in pan and stir.
Cook in 4-quart Dutch oven. Cover and let simmer for 1 hour or can bake in oven.

title: strawberry chiffon pie
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and cool until nearly set.
Whip until frothy.
Beat whipping cream until stiff.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding sugar a tablespoon at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine jello, whipped cream and egg whites.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour into cooled, baked pie shell and place in refrigerator to chill until firm.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Pour brown sugar, cocoa and water into pan. Sprinkle miniature marshmallows over mixture. Mix devil's food cake as directed on box, adding vanilla. Pour over mixture. Sprinkle coarsely chopped pecans over cake mix. Bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 50 minutes or until done. Let cool. Cut in squares and serve with sauce side up.

title: easy oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir together flour, salt, soda and spices. Fold into creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal (and raisins).
Drop dough by rounded spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden.
Do not overbake; the cookies are better when they are slightly soft.

title: ore-ida potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour (or until brown on top and bubbly).

title: corn salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together for sauce.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let chill 1 hour before serving.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, oil and egg.
Combine dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Add baking soda mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Yield:
5 dozen.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening and 1/2 cup powdered sugar well.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Make into balls.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: party favorites
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: granola snack
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: doo dads
directions: Melt margarine in shallow pan over low heat.
Stir in salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cereal and nuts.
Mix until all pieces are coated.
Heat in 250° oven for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.

title: crystal garden
directions: Place briquettes in a shallow bowl.
Mix all ingredients, except the food coloring.
Pour solution over briquettes. Sprinkle food coloring over contents in the bowl.
Once crystals begin growing, you can add more solution and food coloring to watch the garden continually change and grow.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and blend well after each.
Sift flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and bake in tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: chicken tortilla
directions: Line greased 9 x 13-inch casserole with 4 tortillas, then layer chicken, cheese, peppers, onion, etc.
Continue until all ingredients are used.
Thin sour cream with approximately 1 pint of chicken broth.
Make holes in casserole with wooden spoon. Pour sour cream mixture over top and down sides.
Let set for at least 8 hours.

title: chicken pot pie rolls
directions: Saute vegetables in lightly oiled pan.
Add chicken and saute until warm.
Put chicken and vegetables into large mixing bowl; add can of celery soup and mushrooms and set aside.
Roll out crescent rolls onto smooth surface.
Separate rolls into squares, not triangles.
Spoon chicken mixture onto squares and fold sides over top, covering the mixture completely.
Put into rounded deep casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Cover with cream of chicken soup and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until rolls are brown.

title: easy pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, and beat for several minutes.
Pour into 3 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 1\4 hours.

title: spinach madeleine
directions: Cook
spinach
according
to package directions.
Drain and reserve
liquid.
Melt
butter in saucepan; add onion and cook until
tender.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Stir in vegetable liquor and milk slowly, stirring constantly and cook until
thick.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk until almost soft ball on candy thermometer; add peanut butter, marshmallow cream, butter and vanilla.
Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Chill.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Butter and flour two 8-inch round cake pans.
Melt chocolate in a small pot or bowl over simmering water; set aside to cool.
Cream the butter; slowly beat in the sugar until light.
Add the eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Add the chocolate; combine thoroughly.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt; add to the first mixture and blend.
Add 1 cup ice water; beat until smooth.
Pour into pans and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tiger stripes
directions: Line 8 x 8-inch pan with foil.
Grease lightly.
Melt chocolate chips with 2 tablespoons peanut butter over low heat. Stir well.
Pour half of mixture into prepared pan.
Let sit 10 to 15 minutes to cool slightly.
Melt white chocolate with remaining peanut butter over low heat in small saucepan.
Spoon half white chocolate over dark chocolate.
Drop remainder of both by spoonfuls on top.
Run a knife through the pan in a zig zag. Place in freezer for 1 hour.
Break into small pieces.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: Cook broccoli, covered, in 1 can chicken broth in large kettle for about 7 minutes or until just tender.
Remove broccoli from broth; cool and chop coarsely.
Add remaining chicken broth, milk, ham, salt and pepper to broth in kettle.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Stir in remaining ingredients and chopped broccoli; heat just to serving temperature.
Yields about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: soap bubbles
directions: Carefully stir all ingredients together.

title: southern funnel cake
directions: Mix eggs and milk with water.
Add flour, powder and salt. Beat 1 more minute.
Heat oil in 8-inch skillet at 360°.
Take funnel and hold finger over end.
Pour in 1/2 cup mix.
Remove finger and release batter in a circular motion.
Cook about 2 1/2 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn carefully; cook about 1 minute more.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: holiday party dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Cover; chill.
Stir before serving with chips or fresh veggies.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Make and bake cake according to directions.
While still warm, poke holes in cake with a fork.
Mix cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk together and pour over warm cake. Chill. Top with Cool Whip and coconut. May also garnish with pineapple and nuts, if desired.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating after each addition. Add salt and vanilla.
Alternately add milk and dry ingredients. Mix well.
Bake in a Bundt or tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange-stuffed sweet potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; cut an "X" shape about 1 1/2-inches long and 1-inch deep in each potato.
Brush potatoes with orange juice. Fill slits with orange sections; top each with 1 tablespoon brown sugar and a dash of nutmeg.
Wrap each in aluminum foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Roll out and separate rolls.
Cream with mixer:
cream cheese, garlic powder, salt, pepper and onion flakes.
Stir in chicken.

title: 12 hour salad
directions: Place in layers as given. Spread mayonnaise and sugar over top. Sprinkle on cheese and bacon bits.
Refrigerate 6 to 12 hours before serving.

title: watergate dessert (salad)
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding (blend) in large bowl.
Do not drain pineapple. Mix until moist throughout. Gradually add the marshmallows and Cool Whip to the mixture stirring it as you go. Chill and serve.

title: campers' quick breakfast
directions: Grease a large, deep skillet with cooking spray. Cook ground chuck and turkey until done. Drain fat, if any. Add soup. Cover and simmer until hot. Serve over opened hamburger buns. (Toasted buns are even better.) Salad or slaw round out the meal. Serves 2 to 3 people.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream Crisco and oleo, then add sugar, Pet milk and vanilla. Beat with mixer for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain off excess fat.
Add basil, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, tomato sauce and paste. Simmer until thick.
Cook noodles, drain and rinse.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Place half of noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread half of cheese mixture over noodles, half of Mozzarella and half of meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 12.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over hot shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.
Let cool in pan before cutting into squares.
These will freeze very well.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and syrup. Cook for 5 minutes in microwave on High. Add peanuts. Cook 4 minutes if roasted or 5 minutes if raw. Add margarine and vanilla. Cook 2 minutes more. Remove from heat. Add baking soda and stir. Pour onto a cookie sheet that's been thoroughly sprayed with Pam.

title: avocado and tomato topper
directions: In a small bowl, combine avocado, tomato, onion, lemon juice, garlic powder and hot pepper seasoning.
Spoon 1 rounded teaspoonful mixture on each cracker; sprinkle with bacon.
Serve immediately.
Makes 3 dozen appetizers.

title: unusual delicious casserole
directions: Cook noodles 6 minutes in 2 quarts of boiling salt water; drain.
Add butter.
Place half of noodles in bottom of a 2-quart casserole.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package and drain.
Saute meat and onion in a skillet, breaking meat into small pieces, until meat is brown.
Drain.
Stir meat into spaghetti sauce; add garlic and oregano.
Combine with spaghetti; add milk, cheeses and mushrooms. Mix well and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly and just beginning to brown around edges.

title: salmon steaks with a pepper crust
directions: In a sealable plastic bag, combine well the soy sauce, the garlic, the lemon juice and the sugar; add the salmon, coating it well and let it marinate, sealed and chilled, for 30 minutes. Remove the salmon from the bag, discarding the marinade; pat it dry and press 2 teaspoons of the pepper onto each piece of salmon, coating it thoroughly.
In a heavy skillet, heat the oil over moderately high heat until it is hot, but not smoking and in it, saute the salmon for 2 minutes on each side, or until it just flakes.
Transfer the salmon with a slotted spatula to paper towels and let it drain for 30 seconds.
Serves 2.

title: cake pudding
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Take diced, day-old, plain cake and put in casserole.
Pour uncooked custard mix over top. Bake until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: recipe for dressing on potato salad
directions: Bring to a boil; stir and let stand.
Add 2 tablespoons cream.

title: v-8 lasagna
directions: In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, put uncooked noodles in 2 layers. Sprinkle raw or browned hamburger on top.
Add soup, salt, pepper, onion salt and oregano.
Top with 1 cup cheese.
Pour V-8 juice over and then add remaining cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: Shape and combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Place in casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake in oven at 350° for almost an hour.
Makes a great cold sandwich!
(Add pepper jelly to taste.)

title: quail with lemon butter
directions: Make large hamburger patty and place on sheet of tinfoil.
Add chopped onion, potato, sliced carrots, salt and pepper to taste. Fold up and place on hot charcoal or briquets of gas grill for 25 to 30 minutes, or until done.
Serve with ketchup.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Line baking dish with bread pieces and pour melted butter over them.
Mix until bread is coated with butter.
Stir sugar, cloves and salt into tomatoes.
Heat tomatoes to boiling and pour over bread.
Stir to mix bread with tomatoes.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until well-browned.
This dish freezes well.
Serves six.

title: honey wheat bread
directions: Beat yeast, 2 cups white flour, salt, egg, 1/3 cup honey and water for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Add 1/2 cup whole wheat flour and 1 cup white flour.
Beat 1 minute on high speed.
Add 2 cups whole wheat flour all at once.
Mix in.
Gradually add remaining white flour until dough is stiff.
Knead on board 5 to 10 minutes.
Cover with plastic and a towel.
Let stand 20 minutes. Shape into loaves.
Put in greased loaf pans.
Let rise (doubled in size).

title: grandma eichler's clam chowder
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients in juice from clams about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Combine flour and milk; add to vegetable mixture.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens, stirring occasionally.
Add butter.
Stir in clams and scallops. Continue cooking over low heat until clams are heated through and scallops turn white.
Do not boil or overcook scallops.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Chop and simmer onion, green pepper and celery.
Add tomato paste, water and sugar.
Add cooked shrimp.
Turn off heat.
Can be served over rice if desired.

title: waldorf fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss lightly.
Serve on a lettuce leaf if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: joyce's oyster crackers
directions: Combine ingredients in large plastic container with cover and shake until mixed.
No baking or cooking, just munch.

title: southwest black bean chili
directions: Remove casing from sausage; discard.
Crumble sausage.
Cook sausage and onion in a Dutch oven or large saucepan over medium-high heat for 5 to 8 minutes or until onion is crisp-tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated and flavors are blended, stirring occasionally.

title: pot pie dough
directions: Mix well.
Separate into 2 balls; roll out on floured counter or dough board.

title: sausage balls
directions: Put 2 cups Bisquick in large bowl.
Add crumbled sausage and Cheddar cheese.
Mix together and form into balls about 1-inch in size.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for approximately 30 minutes.
Do not let them get too brown.

title: emily's corn pudding(delicious and easy)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in buttered casserole for 1 1/2 hours at 300° to 325°.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Cut in small pieces and put in bottom of pan. Slice cheese thin, layer over chicken.
Crunch chips and put
half over
cheese and chicken.	Mix
tomatoes
and
soup together and pour over chips.
Top with rest
of chips.	Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: beary snack mix
directions: Mix together in a large bowl and serve.
Can be stored in a plastic bag for future use.

title: hot bean salad
directions: Saute onion and crumbled bacon slices together.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: baked apples
directions: Wash and core apples, leaving the blossom end.
Cover bottom of baking dish with 1/4 cup water.
Place apples, blossom end down, in water.
Mix lemon juice and sugar together and fill the cavities with mixture.
Sprinkle nuts and raisins over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and powdered sugar in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple, vanilla and pecans; fold in whipped topping.

title: boyd's pasta salad
directions: When cooking pasta, do not overcook.
Pasta should be firm. Remove from stove and rinse with cold water.
Drain well.
In large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Let chill in refrigerator, then serve with crackers or French bread and olives.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: In a large 12 x 13-inch casserole (buttered), place 1/2 of the
sliced
potatoes, then a layer of 1/2 of ham.	Repeat layers, alternating with onion and green pepper.

title: hamburger special
directions: Fry onions in oil.
Add beef and cook until done.
Add salt, pepper, soup, water and 1 cup of cheese.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Drain and add to other mixture.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
May be frozen for later.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain and rinse sauerkraut well.
Chop
celery, onion and peppers fine.
Melt sugar, vinegar and oil.
Mix all ingredients. (May add more or fewer vegetables for taste and/or color.)
Add celery seed and garlic powder to taste.
Refrigerate.
Marinate overnight for best tasting.

title: cranberry raspberry kiv
directions: Mix drink, wine and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into glasses and add splash of club soda.
Add ice cubes and orange slices.
Serves 6.

title: cherry delights
directions: Mix and chill ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip into slightly beaten egg whites and roll in 2 cups finely chopped nuts. Place on greased baking sheet.
Press candied cherry halves into center.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: home style chicken and dumplings
directions: In a 6-quart Dutch oven combine chicken, celery, carrots, onion, basil, marjoram, bay leaves, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Add 8 cups water.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Remove from heat.
Remove chicken.
Discard bay leaves. Use a metal spoon to skim fat that rises to the surface.
Reserve 1/2 the chicken and broth for another use.
Return remaining chicken and broth to boiling.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare muffin mix according to directions and bake. Fry bacon until crisp; cool and crumble. Lightly toss all the chopped vegetables and bacon together; set aside.

title: frosted cranberry squares
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup and heat until mixture is boiling.
Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid; cool.
Gently stir in ginger ale.
Chill until partly set.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Cut in margarine. Add milk mixture and eggs; mix well.
Put in 12 x 4-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Sprinkle top with 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 tablespoon margarine. Grease and flour pan.

title: potato salad
directions: In a bowl mix vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and mayonnaise. Mix with potatoes, hard-boiled eggs and onion.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a well-greased baking pan, combine ingredients, except cheese.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven and top with cheese.
Return to the oven to melt cheese.
Serves 8 people.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Place pieces of chopped beef under each piece of chicken in casserole dish.
Place strips of bacon on top of chicken or roll bacon around each boneless breast and use toothpick.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Use 3 1/2 or 4-quart microwave casserole bowl.
Microwave oleo until melted (about 1 minute).
Add evaporated milk.
Add sugar. Microwave 3 minutes; stir.
Microwave 2 minutes; stir.
Microwave 3 minutes; stir.
Microwave 2 1/2 minutes and remove from microwave.
Add peanut butter; mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press into pan 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and eggs until smooth. Spread on crumb crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
When cool, spread top with peach pie filling.

title: vegetable pickles
directions: Cut vegetables into bite size pieces and pack in gallon jar.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes after it begins to boil; stir while cooking to keep from burning. Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, nuts, flavoring and peanut butter until mixed well.
Drop on waxed paper or waxed cookie sheet.

title: mandarin chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, grapes, oranges and almonds.
Mix chicken, celery, lemon juice, onion and salt.
Add first mixture to chicken mixture; toss well.
Serve on lettuce.
Garnish with additional orange slices and grape clusters, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: salsa fresca(great with tortilla chips)
directions: Chop everything as finely as you can.
Blend together; set in refrigerator overnight for all flavors to blend well.
Or, if you can't wait, eat it now.

title: chicken cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish in a 400° oven. Combine flour, baking powder and milk in a bowl.
Mix well. Spoon evenly into margarine in dish. Do not mix.

Combine chicken, soup, chicken broth, peas and carrots, and salt and pepper in a bowl. Mix well. Spoon evenly into prepared dish. Do not stir. Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt
margarine.
Beat
egg
and
milk
together.
Add margarine.	Salt
macaroni.
Add to milk mixture.
Put a layer of macaroni, then cheese, more macaroni, then top with cheese. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in some butter until it's done and put in casserole or pan. Put peas on top, then mushroom soup and then Tater Tots. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour until done.

title: aunt peg's crab imperial
directions: Remove any shell or cartilage from crabmeat.
Combine next 5 items.
Pour over crabmeat and mix lightly.
Place in well-greased ramekins.
Top each with 1 teaspoon mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Lightly brown meat, add onion and cook until tender.
Add seasonings, beans and soup; pour into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Cook and then mash potatoes, add milk and egg. Drop in mounds over meat.
(If desired, sprinkle with 1/2 cup shredded cheese.)
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Defrost broccoli and drain off water.
Add salt, pepper and melted
butter.
Mix
in
eggs,
stuffing mix and Parmesan cheese. Leave
in
refrigerator
to 4 hours.
Roll mixture into 1 inch diameter balls and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Mix and chill at least 1 hour.
Shape like strawberries.
Roll in red sugar; dip end in green sugar for leaves and add a stem (slivered almond colored green).
Keep refrigerated.
Keeps well and any flavor of Jell-O may be used and then shaped into desired fruit.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Boil soup with water; turn heat to medium.
Add gelatine slowly while stirring.
Add cream cheese; stir until dissolved. Cool 1/2 hour.
Mix all other ingredients to soup mixture.
Pour in jello mold and chill until hardened.
Serve with crackers.

title: tuna cheese ball
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Add 1/2 of the last two ingredients to the cheese mixture.
Chill.
Form into a ball and roll in remaining parsley flakes and nuts.

title: very low-fat vegetable dip or spread
directions: Place cream cheese in small mixing bowl.
Fold in soup mix. Place in covered container and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before using.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening with electric mixer until fluffy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating until blended each time.
Add vanilla.
Combine flour and soda; add to butter mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Beat at low speed until blended.
Stir in coconut.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into batter.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool on wire racks.
Spread Nutty cream cheese frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake. Garnish with pecans and cherries.
Frosting recipe follows.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook beans as directed.
Drain.
In a 1-quart casserole, combine beans with soup.
Bake uncovered 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with onions during last 5 minutes of baking.

title: three week muffins
directions: Put All-Bran and Shredded Wheat biscuits crumbled in bowl. Pour boiling water over and let set.
Cream shortening with sugar. Add eggs and beat.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add buttermilk.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes. Batter keeps up to 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Bake or boil chicken; shred.
Crush croutons in blender; set aside.
Cut crescent rolls apart.
Melt 1 cube butter; set aside. Cream together cheese, milk and butter with mixer.
Add shredded chicken with garlic salt.
Blend until creamy.
Put 1 tablespoon on crescent roll and dip in butter.
Roll in croutons.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Use chicken broth for gravy.

title: meal in a pie
directions: For Brown Base, combine the first 2 ingredients; stir constantly.
Gradually add the beef broth and pepper sauce. Simmer until sauce thickens and comes to a boil.
Brown hamburg; drain.
Add vegetables and salt.
Mix well.
Combine this and Brown Base sauce.
Bake a pie crust for 10 minutes at 400°.
Pour meat mixture into pie crust.
Mix the cheese, egg and milk together.
Spoon this evenly over mixture in pie plate.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cattlemen's house dressing
directions: Mix well and thin with milk or cream.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil until thickened.
When cool, pour into a baked pie shell.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: almond joy bars
directions: Mix crumbs, powdered sugar and butter.
Press into a long cake pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 300°.
Mix milk and coconut together and spread over crumbs.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips immediately over bars and spread with fork.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute pepper and onions in butter.
Mix all other ingredients. Bake in large casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
